#: 21337012-0-970
msgctxt "21337012-0-970"
msgid "Father,"
"\n"
"\nYou won't understand my reasons for leaving, but you deserve at least to hear them. Maybe you'll reread them eventually and they'll make sense."
"\n"
"\nI am not a mage. My talents in magic, by your own contemptuous admission, are weak. My skills lie elsewhere, and I plan to put them to use. I will never be the prodigal mage you hoped for, but you have never heard me sneak in or out of the house, nor do you likely know that I overheard your comments to your wizard friends over dinner. I know you think little of me, and wish I had been born otherwise, but I have not, and I'll spare you the further burden of my company."
"\n"
"\nI will send money home, a portion of that I make. Whether you find it proof that I am doing well for myself or simply find it useful to put food on your table matters not to me. Consider it slow repayment for the years you have dealt with the burden of an underachieving son."
"\n"
"\nI love you dearly, Father, but I cannot abide your company. Live well."
"\n"
"\nYour son,"
"\n"
"\nTamien"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-970
msgctxt "51188213-0-970"
msgid "Letter From Tamien Sellan"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-962
msgctxt "21337012-0-962"
msgid "Egranor,"
"\n"
"\nI know. You said never to contact you. But what happened at Quendeluun … I didn't sign up to be a traitor. The Heritance in bed with the Ebonheart Pact? It flies in the face of everything I believe. You must report this."
"\n"
"\nI can only assume that Earran has taken a more extreme turn. I'll write to my mother, have her relay the information to the Queen. "
"\n"
"\nGreenshade seems so far from Auridon. I miss home. I miss the Summerset Isles."
"\n"
"\nI miss you. I'm sorry."
"\n"
"\n— Aranias"
msgstr "에그라노어,"
"\n"
"\n나도 알아. 너한테 절대 연락하지 말라고 했지. 하지만 퀜델룬에서 일어났던 일은... 난 배신자가 된 게 아니야. 계승단이 에본하트 조약과 한 침대를 쓰고 있다니? 그건 내가 믿었던 모든 것들과는 반대되는 일이야. 넌 이 사실을 보고해야 해."
"\n"
"\n나는 이란이 더 극단적인 방향으로 나아가고 있다는 것만 추측할 수 있을 뿐이야. 난 어머니께 편지를 써서 이 정보를 여왕님께 전달하도록 할게."
"\n"
"\n그린쉐이드는 아우리돈에서 너무 먼 것만 같아. 집이 그리워. 서머셋 군도가 그리워."
"\n"
"\n네가 그리워. 미안해."
"\n"
"\n— 아라니아스"

#: 51188213-0-962
msgctxt "51188213-0-962"
msgid "Letter to Egranor"
msgstr "에그라노어에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-951
msgctxt "21337012-0-951"
msgid "I don't care how, but I want that drugged wamasu out of the hold and under <<1>>. It should fit through the old Imperial aquifer outside the city walls. If we can't secure our escape route before the ritual completes, we're sunk."
"\n"
"\nAnd don't jostle it! If it wakes angry, it starts melting support columns. We don't want the city to come down until after we're gone."
"\n"
"\n— <<2>>"
msgstr "어떻게 하는지는 상관 없어. 그 약에 취한 와마수를 가지고 <<1>> 아래로 가라. 도시 벽 바깥에 있는 옛 제국 대수층을 통해서 들어갈 수 있을거야. 의식이 완료되기 전에 우리 탈출 경로를 확보하지 못한다면, 우린 끝장나는 거다."
"\n"
"\n그리고 와마수를 거칠게 떠밀지 마라! 녀석이 화난 채로 깨어나면 지지대 기둥을 녹여버리기 시작할 거다. 우리가 일을 끝낼 때 까지는 도시가 주저앉으면 안 된다."
"\n"
"\n— <<2>>"

#: 51188213-0-951
msgctxt "51188213-0-951"
msgid "Gjarma's Orders: Wamasu"
msgstr "기얄마의 명령서: 와마수"

#: 21337012-0-950
msgctxt "21337012-0-950"
msgid "Let your lot fill their pouches, but the necromancers will need bodies for the plan to work. Ten cart-loads should be enough."
"\n"
"\nAnd look for bodies in the streets before you go about making any new ones. If the people of <<1>> see us bashing down their doors and dragging out corpses, they'll find courage beneath their fear."
"\n"
"\n— <<2>>"
msgstr "주머니에 네 몫을 채우는 것도 좋지만, 강령술사들이 계획을 진행하려면 시체가 필요하다. 수레 열 개 정도면 충분할 거야."
"\n"
"\n그리고 새로운 시체를 만들어내기 전에 거리에 있는 시체들부터 찾아봐라. 우리가 문을 박살내고 들어가서 시체를 끌고 나오는 모습을 <<1>> 사람들이 본다면, 공포 아래에 억눌렸던 용기가 되살아날 테니까."
"\n"
"\n— <<2>>"

#: 51188213-0-950
msgctxt "51188213-0-950"
msgid "Gjarma's Orders: Supplies"
msgstr "기얄마의 명령서: 물자"

#: 21337012-0-949
msgctxt "21337012-0-949"
msgid "I understand your concern about lack of supplies for the ritual. But you're forgetting there's a local Mages Guild to raid for stores."
"\n"
"\nOnce you confirm they have the goods, send me word so we know to proceed."
"\n"
"\n— <<1>>"
msgstr "의식에 필요한 물자가 부족하다는 네 걱정은 이해한다만, 현지 메이지 길드에 털어먹을 비축품이 있다는 사실을 깜빡한 모양이구나."
"\n"
"\n길드에 물자가 있는지 확인해 보고, 계획을 진행할 수 있을지 소식을 전해라."
"\n"
"\n— <<1>>"

#: 51188213-0-949
msgctxt "51188213-0-949"
msgid "Gjarma's Orders: Yngold"
msgstr "기얄마의 명령서: 잉골드"

#: 21337012-0-94
msgctxt "21337012-0-94"
msgid "Grularz,"
"\n"
"\nYou have always been a dreamer, my sister, and I've love that about you. As mad as some of your schemes have been, I have always tried to encourage you."
"\n"
"\nBut this time is different. Trolls are dangerous creatures! I fear that this dream will be your last if you do not abandon it and come home. Since you have refused me several times now, I assume this letter will also fail to change your mind, so I am just going to have to let go. I will always love you, sister."
"\n"
"\n— Gothurg"
msgstr "Grularz,"
"\n"
"\n내 자매여, 당신은 항상 꿈꾸는 자였고 나는 당신의 그 점을 사랑했습니다. 당신의 계획이 얼마나 미쳤든, 나는 항상 당신을 지지할려고 노력했습니다."
"\n"
"\n그러나 이번 상황은 다릅니다. 트롤은 위험한 생명체 입니다! 나는 당신이 이 꿈을 포기하지 않고 집으로 돌아오지 않는다면, 이번 꿈이 당신에게 마지막이 될까봐 두렵습니다. 당신이 이미 여러번 나의 편지를 거절했던 사실을 가장하면, 나는 이 편지 또한 당신의 결정을 바꾸는데 실패할 것이라고 생각합니다. 결국 나는 당신이 꿈을 이행하도록 놔둘 것입니다.  자매여, 나는 항상 당신을 사랑합니다."
"\n"
"\n—Gothurg으로 부터"
"\n"

#: 51188213-0-94
msgctxt "51188213-0-94"
msgid "Letter from Gothurg"
msgstr "Gothurg로 부터의 편지"

#: 21337012-0-932
msgctxt "21337012-0-932"
msgid "Merormo, you are no longer welcome at the college. Your continued ill-advised experiments—after repeated  warnings—have forced my hand. "
"\n"
"\nPlease pack your things and vacate the premises at once. "
"\n"
"\n— Telenger"
msgstr "메로모. 너는 더 이상 학교에서 환영받지 못할 것이다. 경고를 계속 했음에도 불구하고 경솔한 실험을 계속하니 내가 손을 쓸 수밖에 없구나."
"\n"
"\n네 짐을 싸서 즉시 방을 비워주길 바란다."
"\n"
"\n— 텔렌저"

#: 51188213-0-932
msgctxt "51188213-0-932"
msgid "Dismissal Letter"
msgstr "해고 편지"

#: 21337012-0-903
msgctxt "21337012-0-903"
msgid "Dear Sir,"
"\n"
"\nA kind gentleman delivered a copy of your fine pamphlet entitled "A Visit to High Kinlord Rilis XII's Court." In this magnificent volume, you demonstrated your masterful vocabulary whilst describing the various foibles of my liege's court. "
"\n"
"\nI was particularly fond of your kind praise of my jesterly performances, especially the act you described as "abominably distasteful" and "prurient nonsense." I applaud your honesty and forthrightness. Like any great artist, I can appreciate the constructive criticism. "
"\n"
"\nI would like to invite you to my lodgings. Upon your arrival, I will throw you down a flight of stairs repeatedly. My goal is to break your neck, and to see the last flicker of life extinguished from your vast, empty eyes. "
"\n"
"\nYours respectfully, "
"\n"
"\nFalarel"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-903
msgctxt "51188213-0-903"
msgid "To My Reviewer"
msgstr "저의 논평가에게"

#: 21337012-0-866
msgctxt "21337012-0-866"
msgid "Dear Mother,"
"\n"
"\nTomorrow we land at Murkwater. I'm nervous … sure, I've trained. But this is our first engagement on foreign soil. Well, foreign mud."
"\n"
"\nThe soldiers I'm with are a motley band. We Altmer are disciplined and respect the chain of command. But the Renrijra and the Oathbreakers are another story."
"\n"
"\nThe Renrijra are Khajiiti privateers. They're very relaxed. No drilling, no inspections … but if you make one mad, she fights like one fierce bastard. They're good to spend some downtime with, as we did up the coast while we were waiting for the Bosmer. Don't worry, I didn't try any moon sugar."
"\n"
"\nEverybody always says the Oathbreakers are Bosmer barbarians. (Except for Captain Pamolwen. Privileges of rank, I guess.) They eat vegetables, carve wood, all of that. You'd think without primitive traditions, they'd be happy, but they're a grim bunch. They and the Khajiit avoid each other."
"\n"
"\nI tried their meat alcohol, since we weren't allowed to bring any wine of our own. The "rotmeth" was nasty at first, but you get used to it."
"\n"
"\nHow will we hold together when we actually land? These Argonians are civilians, but there'll be a lot of them. Shadowfen seems alien and dangerous. Some of the animals, you'd think came from Morrowind. Those who live with such creatures must be pretty tough. Glad we're starting with a soft target."
"\n"
"\nGive my love to the cousins."
"\n"
"\nYour devoted son,"
"\nFilpinil"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-866
msgctxt "51188213-0-866"
msgid "Letter Home"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-833
msgctxt "21337012-0-833"
msgid "Razum-dar,"
"\n"
"\nThe usual channels weren't working. Be apprised: The college has been compromised. The headmaster, Tanion, now wears the Veil. Zaban was not sure at first. Now confirmed. "
"\n"
"\nThe Veiled Queen herself controls this place. Send agents now."
"\n"
"\nZaban"
msgstr "라줌-다르,"
"\n"
"\n평시 연락망이 작동하지 않는군요. 보고 드리죠. 학교가 위태로워졌습니다. 교장 타니온은 이제 베일을 썼습니다. 자반은 처음엔 확신하지 못했었죠. 지금은 확실합니다."
"\n"
"\n"
"\n여기는 베일의 여왕이 직접 통제하고 있습니다. 당장 요원들을 보내십시오."
"\n"
"\n자반"

#: 51188213-0-833
msgctxt "51188213-0-833"
msgid "Zaban's Letter"
msgstr "자반의 편지"

#: 21337012-0-738
msgctxt "21337012-0-738"
msgid "Raen,"
"\n"
"\nThings are strange here in Silvenar. More Green Hunters walk the streets than usual, and they're belligerent. I've heard the Green Lady arrived in the city, but we've not seen her. The three spinners are likewise closeted and their messages are cryptic and frightening."
"\n"
"\nUrge the Silvenar to come quickly! Rely on speed, not soldiers! They say the Green Lady prepares for the handfast, but who can she marry if not the Silvenar?"
"\n"
"\nI hope to see you soon. Perhaps I worry for nothing, but something seems wrong in Malabal Tor."
"\n"
"\n— Berfonas"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-738
msgctxt "51188213-0-738"
msgid "Letter from Berfonas"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-661
msgctxt "21337012-0-661"
msgid "We tried to smuggle in some Springwater wine to help bolster your spirits. The guards took it from us, though. "
"\n"
"\nDon't worry: As soon as you're out of there, we'll throw you a great, big party. Drinks on me."
"\n"
"\n— Minique"
msgstr "네 기분을 좀 좋게 해 주려고 우리가 샘물 포도주를 몰래 들여오려고 했단다. 그런데 경비병이 압수해갔지 뭐니."
"\n"
"\n걱정 말렴. 네가 거기서 나오는 대로 굉장하고 커다란 파티를 열어줄 테니까. 술은 내가 쏘마."
"\n"
"\n— 미니크"

#: 51188213-0-661
msgctxt "51188213-0-661"
msgid "Letter from Minique"
msgstr "미니크가 보낸 편지"

#: 21337012-0-660
msgctxt "21337012-0-660"
msgid "Son, don't worry. I know you were scared when you went down there, but everything will be all right."
"\n"
"\nYour friend from down the road just got the salve yesterday. Maybe he'll be joining you soon? I know you wouldn't want him to get sick, but I'd feel better with someone watching out for you."
"\n"
"\nKeep yourself safe, and dream of the Stars."
"\n"
"\nWe'll see you soon."
"\n"
"\n— Lenwe"
msgstr "아들아, 걱정 말거라. 네가 그 아래로 내려갈 때 얼마나 두려워했는지 잘 알지만, 모든 것이 잘 될거란다."
"\n"
"\n아랫집에 사는 네 친구도 어제 연고를 받았단다. 아마 조만간 너랑 만나지 않겠니? 그 친구가 아프지 않길 바라는 네 마음을 알지만, 누군가 널 돌봐줄 사람이 생겼다니 엄마는 좀 더 안심이 되는구나."
"\n"
"\n몸 조심히 잘 있거라. 별님 꿈 꾸고."
"\n"
"\n우린 곧 만날 수 있을 거야."
"\n"
"\n— 렌웨"

#: 51188213-0-660
msgctxt "51188213-0-660"
msgid "Letter from Lenwe"
msgstr "렌웨가 보낸 편지"

#: 21337012-0-659
msgctxt "21337012-0-659"
msgid "Dearest sister,"
"\n"
"\nJust like we thought, Father was the one stealing the loaves from the cupboard. Mother yelled and yelled, and we laughed and laughed. We would have laughed harder with you there. "
"\n"
"\nGet well, little sis. Auri-El watch over you."
"\n"
"\n— Camarino"
msgstr "가장 사랑하는 내 여동생에게,"
"\n"
"\n우리 예상대로 찬장에서 빵을 훔친 건 아버지였어. 어머닌 고래고래 소리 지르셨고, 우린 실컷 웃었지. 너도 함께 있었다면 더 크게, 실컷 웃을 수 있었을 거야."
"\n"
"\n사랑하는 동생아, 잘 지내렴. 아우리-엘께서 널 굽어보시기를."
"\n"
"\n— 카마리노"

#: 51188213-0-659
msgctxt "51188213-0-659"
msgid "Letter from Camarino"
msgstr "카마리노가 보낸 편지"

#: 21337012-0-640
msgctxt "21337012-0-640"
msgid "To Whom it May Concern:"
"\n"
"\nI heard through a friend that you may be hiring at the College of Aldmeri Propriety. I believe my vast knowledge and experience in the culture and etiquette make me extremely qualified for the job. I've spent the last five years as a tutor among nobility."
"\n"
"\nExperience: "
"\n— Tutored for the Rilis family for five years."
"\n— Well practiced in social skills."
"\n— Extensive classes in etiquette."
"\n— Wide knowledge of Aldmeri history and Altmer views."
"\n"
"\nPlease consider my applicaton for the position. I look forward to hearing from you."
"\n"
"\nSincerely,"
"\n"
"\nColassewen of Firsthold"
msgstr "관심을 가지실 분께"
"\n"
"\n알드메리 예절 학교에서 사람을 고용중이라고 친구에게 들었습니다. 제가 가진 문화와 예절에 대한 방대한 지식과 경험은 제가 그 직업을 가질 아주 큰 자격을 부여해 준다고 생각합니다. 저는 지난 5년을 귀족들 사이에서 가정교사로 보내왔습니다."
"\n"
"\n경력:"
"\n— 5년 동안 릴리스 가문에서 가정교사로 일함."
"\n— 사회성 기술에 숙달됨."
"\n— 예절에 대한 광범위한 강좌 수료."
"\n— 알드메리 역사와 알트머의 사고방식에 대한 폭넓은 지식."
"\n"
"\n저의 직무 신청서를 고려해 주시길 바랍니다. 답장을 기다리고 있겠습니다."
"\n"
"\n진심을 담아,"
"\n"
"\n퍼스트홀드의 콜라세웬"

#: 51188213-0-640
msgctxt "51188213-0-640"
msgid "Faculty Application"
msgstr "학부 신청서"

#: 21337012-0-638
msgctxt "21337012-0-638"
msgid "My Dear Estre,"
"\n"
"\nIt pains me to know of your opposition to Ayrenn. While I can see your view on maintaining the purity of the Summerset Isles, I cannot disregard the importance of what our queen is trying to do."
"\n"
"\nAs I have a close relationship with both of you, I am unable to take sides in your argument. Firsthold shall remain neutral, and our priorities lie solely in the protection of Auridon from our enemies."
"\n"
"\nWhich are numerous."
"\n"
"\nRegrettably,"
"\n"
"\nRilis XIII, Kinlord"
msgstr "친애하는 에스트리,"
"\n"
"\n당신이 아이렌에게 반대한다는 것을 알게 되어 고통스럽소. 서머셋 군도를 순수하게 유지하고자 하는 당신의 견해는 알겠지만, 우리의 여왕께서 하려 하시는 일에 대한 중요성을 무시할 수는 없소."
"\n"
"\n나는 여왕님과 당신 양쪽 모두와 밀접한 관계를 가지고 있으니, 당신의 편만을 들어줄 수는 없겠소. 퍼스트홀드는 중립으로 남을 것이며, 우리의 우선 순위는 오로지 적들로부터 아우리돈을 지켜내는 일이 될 것이오."
"\n"
"\n수많은 적들로부터 말이오."
"\n"
"\n유감을 담아,"
"\n"
"\n혈족군주, 릴리스 13세"

#: 51188213-0-638
msgctxt "51188213-0-638"
msgid "Letter to Estre"
msgstr "에스트리에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-637
msgctxt "21337012-0-637"
msgid "My most esteemed colleague, Telenger the Artificer,"
"\n"
"\nIt's with great pride that I send you a recommendation for Vinandalin Aonudar. Vinandalin has proven himself very capable in six schools of magic. He's excelled beyond his fellow classmates and is ready for the field. I realize you have many candidates to choose from, but Vinandalin would surprise even you if he were chosen to study. "
"\n"
"\nHere in the Firsthold, he's been promoted from the rank of Student to Apprentice. We're all very proud of him! I assure you, if Vinandalin were chosen, he would not disappoint."
"\n"
"\nRegards, "
"\n"
"\nNamolelcare, Firsthold Hall Steward"
"\n"
"\nP.S.: I hope Meldil is working out well for you, and all is well in the south. Be sure to pass us a copy of your writings on Ezduiin!"
msgstr "가장 존경받으시는 동료, 명장 텔렌저님께"
"\n"
"\n제가 비난달린 아오누다의 추천장을 보내드리게 되어 굉장한 영광이라고 생각합니다. 비난달린은 여섯 학파의 마법에 매우 유능함을 스스로 증명해냈습니다. 동기생들보다 훨씬 뛰어나며 현장에서 일할 준비가 되어 있죠. 저도 명장께서 선택하실 수 있는 후보자들이 많다는 것은 알지만, 비난달린을 공부시키기로 선택하신다면 명장님을 놀라게 해 드릴 겁니다."
"\n"
"\n여기 퍼스트홀드에서 비난달린은 학생에서 견습생의 지위까지 올라갔습니다. 저희 모두가 그를 아주 자랑스러워하죠! 제가 장담컨대, 비난달린을 선택하신다면 실망하지 않으실 겁니다."
"\n"
"\n이만 줄이겠습니다."
"\n"
"\n퍼스트홀드 청지기, 나몰렐카레"
"\n"
"\n추신: 멜딜이 명장님을 도와 일을 잘 하고 있기를 바라고, 남쪽에서의 일이 모두 순조롭기를 바랍니다. 에즈두인에 대한 기록 사본을 꼭 보내주십시오!"

#: 51188213-0-637
msgctxt "51188213-0-637"
msgid "Letter to Telenger"
msgstr "텔렌저에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-565
msgctxt "21337012-0-565"
msgid "Yrna, "
"\n"
"\nLife at Tal'Deic Fortress never gets dull! In my previous letter, I told you all about the Dremora that replaced poor General Redoran. Well, now I'm practically running this place! "
"\n"
"\nOh, the Skald King continues to send me specific agendas to promote and messages to deliver, but Captain Doronil has turned to me to help get the fort back in working order. Maybe things will slow down once a new general is assigned, and then I can come home for a visit. When was the last time I was in Eastmarch? Do you even remember, because I don't! "
"\n"
"\nI so wanted to get back for the Konunleikar, but that just isn't possible. Will you be participating in any of the games? You used to be fairly decent at archery, if I remember correctly. And flirting with visitors to the city. Is that still an event you can sign up for? (Just kidding, little sister!) "
"\n"
"\nWell, time to get back to work. I have troops to inspect and all that. Give my best to mother and father. "
"\n"
"\n— Ragna"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-565
msgctxt "51188213-0-565"
msgid "Letter from Ragna"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-541
msgctxt "21337012-0-541"
msgid "To The Veiled Queen, Future Ruler Of Auridon"
"\n"
"\nOur plan to use South Beacon as a staging area for our occupation of Auridon is in motion. The lighthouse is now under our control and a powerful magical ward will limit entry to all but our most trusted agents."
"\n"
"\nAs per our previous discussions, you will continue to supply updated, detailed information regarding the navigation of Auridon Strait and the scheduled fleet movements of Altmer Naval vessels in the area to our agents in South Beacon. They will relay the information to our ships, in code, using the lighthouse beacon. "
"\n"
"\nIn recompense for this aid, you will be named our Viceroy of Auridon once our control of Summerset is assured. "
"\n"
"\nMay Your Prow Ride High, "
"\n"
"\nSealord Malleroth Of Pyandonea"
"\nMaormer High Command"
msgstr "아우리돈의 미래의 지도자, 베일의 여왕께"
"\n"
"\n아우리돈을 점령하기 위해 남부 신호소를 우리의 집결지로 사용하는 계획은 진행 중입니다. 등대는 이제 우리의 통제 하에 있으며 강력한 마법 방어장이 우리의 가장 신뢰받는 요원 말고는 들어가지 못하게 할 것입니다."
"\n"
"\n이전에 했던 논의대로, 남부 신호소에 있는 우리 요원들에게 계속해서 물자를 보급해 주시고, 아우리돈 해협의 뱃길과 알트머 해군 선박들의 이동 일정에 대한 세부 정보를 제공해 주십시오. 요원들이 등대 신호소로 암호를 보내서 우리 함선들에게 정보를 전달할 것입니다."
"\n"
"\n이 도움의 대가로서, 우리가 서머셋을 확실하게 통제하고 나면 당신은 아우리돈의 총독으로 불리게 될 것입니다."
"\n"
"\n당신의 뱃머리가 높이 뜨기를."
"\n"
"\n피안도네아의 바다군주 말레로스"
"\n마오머 고위 사령관"

#: 51188213-0-541
msgctxt "51188213-0-541"
msgid "To The Veiled Queen"
msgstr "베일의 여왕께"

#: 21337012-0-524
msgctxt "21337012-0-524"
msgid "Dear Mother,"
"\n"
"\nEssanyon is insane. I first thought he sought a path in life. Now he talks only of the end of days. He speaks of the crow he sees in his dreams. He can't distinguish between the real and the unreal. "
"\n"
"\nHe now believes the end of the world is at hand, as I'm sure he's written you. He has told me that sacrificing a Skywatch noble will somehow thwart this End. I can't allow him to murder another for the sake of his delusory faith."
"\n"
"\nI must report him to the Skywatch Guard. And come what may, I must stop him. I'm sorry. I love you as always, but I must stop him."
"\n"
"\n— Quaronaldil"
msgstr "사랑하는 어머니,"
"\n"
"\n에사니온은 미쳤습니다. 처음에는 동생이 인생의 길을 찾았다고 생각했어요. 이제는 종말의 날만을 이야기하고 있군요. 에사니온은 자기가 꿈에서 보는 까마귀에 대한 이야기를 하고 있어요. 현실과 비현실 사이를 구별하지 못하고 있습니다."
"\n"
"\n이제는 세상의 종말이 가까웠다고 믿고 있어요. 분명 동생도 어머니께 그런 내용의 편지를 썼겠죠. 에사니온이 저에게 스카이워치의 귀족들을 희생시키면 어떻게든 그 종말을 막아낼 수 있다고 했었어요. 동생이 자신의 또 다른 망상적인 신념을 위해서 살인을 저지르도록 할 수는 없습니다."
"\n"
"\n스카이워치 경비대에 신고해야 합니다. 어떤 어려움이 있어도 에사니온을 막아야 해요. 죄송해요. 저는 언제나처럼 어머니를 사랑하지만, 저는 반드시 동생을 막아야만 합니다."
"\n"
"\n— 쿼로나딜"

#: 51188213-0-524
msgctxt "51188213-0-524"
msgid "Quaronaldil's Letter"
msgstr "쿼로나딜의 편지"

#: 21337012-0-490
msgctxt "21337012-0-490"
msgid "My Lord Fildgor,"
"\n"
"\nThe contingent of Stormfist warriors you assigned to my command perform superbly. We've been disrupting trade and travel throughout the area, just as you ordered. When you give the signal, we'll begin the march toward Windhelm. We'll be in position to surround the city when the time comes to attack. "
"\n"
"\nI wish I could be with you at Skuldafn, but I understand how important my mission is and why you entrusted me with accomplishing it."
"\n"
"\nI can't wait to bend my knee before you and witness the moment when you take your place upon the throne. If you would honor me with the task, I would love to make your cursed brother Jorunn pay for his crimes against you. "
"\n"
"\nThat milk-drinking bard! How he defeated you in battle is beyond me, Strong-Prince. You should have torn him apart like a rag doll. I know he cheated. I just know it!"
"\n"
"\nWe cleared the Goblins out of the Bastard's Tomb and have turned the place into a rather comfortable headquarters for the Brigade. But I'm afraid the soft living is starting to make my troops lazy. Don't worry, though. I'll beat that out of them quickly."
"\n"
"\nMy troops are itching to do more than maraud across the countryside. We long for a real battle against worthy opponents! Hopefully, the skeevers guarding Windhelm will provide just the challenge we need."
"\n"
"\nUntil I am once again by your side, I remain,"
"\n"
"\n— Agenor Storm-Blade"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-490
msgctxt "51188213-0-490"
msgid "Letter from Agenor"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-4576
msgctxt "21337012-0-4576"
msgid "Dear <<1>>,"
"\n"
"\nHonored friend, the most-revered and holy Vivec, Warrior-Poet of the Tribunal, has taken notice of your exploits and requests a meeting. Make your way to Morrowind and the great island of Vvardenfell as soon as you can. Look for me outside the town of Seyda Neen. I'll escort you to Vivec City and introduce you to our immortal god-king."
"\n"
"\nCaptain Jenassa's ship to Seyda Neen leaves from Daggerfall, Davon's Watch, Vulkhel Guard, and other cities around Tamriel. Or you can take a boat from Mournhold, Wayrest, or Woodhearth to Vivec City."
"\n"
"\nCanon Llevule,"
"\nPriest of the Tribunal,"
"\nAide to Archcanon Tarvus"
msgstr "<<1>> 에게,"
"\n"
"\n트라이뷰널의 전사이자 시인인, 가장 존경받는 신성한 비벡의 친구로서 편지를 드립니다. 당신의 활약이 비벡의 귀에 들어가면서 비벡이 당신을 만나고 싶어합니다. 되도록 빨리 모로윈드의 위대한 섬 바덴펠로 와주셨으면 합니다. 세이다 닌의 마을 밖에서 저를 찾아주세요. 비벡 시로 모셔서 불사의 신이자 저희의 왕을 소개해 드리겠습니다."
"\n"
"\n자네사 선장의 배가 대거폴, Davon's Watch, Vulkhel Guard, 및 탐리엘의 기타 도시에서 세이다 닌으로 향합니다. 혹은 Mournhold, 웨이래스트, Woodhearth에서 보트를 타고 비벡 시로 와주셔도 됩니다."
"\n"
"\n트라이뷰널의 사제이자,"
"\nArchcanon Tarvus의 보좌관,"
"\nCanon Llevule 드림"

#: 51188213-0-4576
msgctxt "51188213-0-4576"
msgid "Invitation to Morrowind"
msgstr "모로윈드로의 초대장"

#: 21337012-0-4570
msgctxt "21337012-0-4570"
msgid "To the Arch-Mage, on Eyevea,"
"\n"
"\nI pray that this letter reaches you soon, master. My fellow scryers and I have made a shocking discovery. Whether it proves to be a boon or a catastrophe remains to be seen.  Alas, we do not wield sufficient power to act on our findings. This matter may be beyond the ken of even the greatest wizards of our age!"
"\n"
"\nI humbly beseech you: meet me at the Mages Guildhall in Mournhold as soon as possible. I will tell you everything when you arrive."
"\n"
"\nYours in the Sight of Syrabane,"
"\nDocent Skaldir, Associate Scryer of the Order of the Eye"
msgstr "아이베아에서 대마법사님께,"
"\n"
"\n이 편지가 곧 당신께 닿기를 빕니다, 스승님. 동료 점쟁이들과 제가 충격적인 발견을 했습니다. 그것이 선물이 될지 재앙이 될지는 아직 밝혀지지 않았습니다. 아아, 저희는 이 발견에 대한 행동을 취할 정도로 충분한 힘을 가지지 못하였습니다. 이 문제는 우리 시대의 가장 위대한 마법사들의 이해를 넘어서는 것일지도 모릅니다!"
"\n"
"\n겸손하게 간청드립니다. 가능한 빨리 모운홀드 메이지 길드 회관에서 저를 만나 주십시오. 도착하시면 모든 것을 말씀드리겠습니다."
"\n"
"\n시라바네의 시야에 들어 계시길,"
"\n눈의 조직 소속 준학사 점쟁이, 강사 스칼디어"

#: 51188213-0-4570
msgctxt "51188213-0-4570"
msgid "Order of the Eye Dispatch"
msgstr "눈의 조직 급보"

#: 21337012-0-4564
msgctxt "21337012-0-4564"
msgid "Cousin,"
"\n"
"\nI know you've got a place above that store in Stormwind, but you really have to join me in Vvardenfell. I've been here less than a year and I've already got my own place just outside Balmora. I'm making enough gold that I take voyages down to Vivec City every month or so."
"\n"
"\nYou wouldn't believe the architecture here. They built "the City of the Warrior-Poet" right out on the water. All these multi-layered cantons—I have a hard time finding my way around!"
"\n"
"\nAnd Balmora has a canal running right through the center of the town. I though they'd call it the "town of waters," but it really should be "the town of beautiful barmaids." There's a Dark Elf woman working at one of the inns who really likes me, I can tell."
"\n"
"\nAnyway, when you get here, find me in Balmora. It's north of Seyda Neen. If you land in Vivec City, spend the extra gold for a barge trip. The wildlife along the road can be a bit dangerous."
"\n"
"\nArturian"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-4564
msgctxt "51188213-0-4564"
msgid "Come to Vvardenfell!"
msgstr "바덴펠로 오라!"

#: 21337012-0-4560
msgctxt "21337012-0-4560"
msgid "This month's Tribunal Temple Profile shines a bright light on our own high priest in the service of Lord Vivec—Archcanon Tarvus! Yours truly, Seventy-sixth Adjuvant Drumara, sat down to interview the busy cleric in his well-appointed office in the Hall of Wisdom, in the canton directly across from Vivec's Palace in Vivec City."
"\n"
"\nAdjuvant Drumara: Thank you for agreeing to talk with me, Archcanon. The faithful who regularly read our weekly missives have been asking to learn more about the Dunmer who keeps the Temple and the city running smoothly."
"\n"
"\nArchcanon Tarvus: Lord Vivec and the Tribunal keep the wheels turning. I am merely their servant."
"\n"
"\nAdjuvant Drumara: Modest, as always! How did you find your way to a life of religious service?"
"\n"
"\nArchcanon Tarvus: I grew up in House Indoril, so while a role in the Temple wasn't guaranteed, it was certainly strongly encouraged. I found that the words of the Warrior-Poet moved me, and I quickly gravitated toward serving Lord Vivec. Here's a secret few people know—I almost dedicated myself to the Buoyant Armigers. The call to adventure appealed to my younger self, and I even fancied myself something of a poet. Lord Vivec, however, had other plans for me."
"\n"
"\nAdjuvant Drumara: So it's true that Lord Vivec himself recruited you into his priesthood?"
"\n"
"\nArchcanon Tarvus: Let's not make the story more significant than the reality. I was a young acolyte, training for a life of service in the Temple. When the time came to choose a path, Lord Vivec talked to me and suggested I would do better in the priesthood than as a swashbuckling Armiger or a militaristic Ordinator. I meditated on my choice and discovered, deep in my heart, that I agreed with him."
"\n"
"\nAdjuvant Drumara: And then you demonstrated a real talent for both spiritual and administrative labors, rising to become the youngest canon ever to attain the rank of archcanon?"
"\n"
"\nArchcanon Tarvus: Young? I suppose so. But that was so long ago. I worked hard, constantly demonstrating my devotion to Vivec, the Three, and the people of Morrowind. That Lord Vivec saw fit to reward me with this honor and this responsibility, well, you'd have to ask him why I of all the canons was ultimately selected to replace my predecessor. I am just grateful for the opportunity to help my Lord and serve my Temple."
"\n"
"\nAdjuvant Drumara: Your sermons on the dangers of outlanders in Vvardenfell can be quite stirring. Do you think our land really faces a threat from those who come with different cultures and beliefs?"
"\n"
"\nArchcanon Tarvus: For a minor priest and functionary, you tend to ask leading questions. My views on outlanders, however, are quite well known and completely consistent. No one other than the Dark Elves can claim such a unique relationship as we have with our Living Gods. That gives us a perspective and outlook on life that is, in fact, superior to every other culture in Tamriel. We are stronger when we are pure, when our culture isn't polluted by the thoughts and ideas of the lesser peoples. But other than that, I have nothing against the occasional outlander visiting our fair and beautiful island of Vvardenfell. "To challenge the strange allows us to know our strength," as the Warrior-Poet has written."
"\n"
"\nAdjuvant Drumara: One of your closest aides, Canon Llevule Andrano, has been quoted as saying that you "carry the burden of Lord Vivec and the entire palace atop your shoulders." Do you agree with his assessment?"
"\n"
"\nArchcanon Tarvus: Is it a burden to serve the Warrior-Poet? Is it an obligation to make sure the business of the palace and the Temple and the city progresses smoothly and without stumble? I do what I do for my love of the Tribunal and its people. That is not a burden, Adjuvant Drumara, that is a rare and singular privilege! I do my best to instill that same attitude in all of the priests that serve under my administration. You would do well to remember that, as I am quite certain you fit into that category."
"\n"
"\nAdjuvant Drumara: Of course, Archcanon Tarvus. I simply asked so that I could quote you accurately. May I ask one more question before we conclude this interview?"
"\n"
"\nArchcanon Tarvus: If you must."
"\n"
"\nAdjuvant Drumara: How is the work on Vivec City coming along?"
"\n"
"\nArchcanon Tarvus: Construction on Lord Vivec's metropolis proceeds just as the Warrior-Poet has commanded. The cantons take shape like islands in the bay. The ziggurats rise as though to touch Baar Dau itself. It is already a masterpiece, and it is not yet nearly half done! Vivec City is already the envy of every other nation in Tamriel. Imagine the accolades we shall receive as it nears completion! Now, if we're done here, I have the business of Lord Vivec to get back to."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-4560
msgctxt "51188213-0-4560"
msgid "Archcanon Tarvus Interview"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-446
msgctxt "21337012-0-446"
msgid "Dearest Cousin Jakild,"
"\n"
"\nHow's that husband of yours? Still treating you well? And his annoying brother, Kerthor? Still annoying, I'm sure! Are there really enough trees in that part of the tundra for you to make a decent living? And the weather, are the days as gray as the ones in Windhelm?"
"\n"
"\nI hope you're taking care of my little sister. You know how much Agnedir looks up to you. Of all the cousins, you've always been her favorite. Make sure she also keeps up with her forester training!"
"\n"
"\nHave you had any luck finding her a decent suitor? There's a logging camp to your east. I know some of the loggers. They're good people. But what about those neighbors you wrote to me about? The ones directly to your west? The rich ones? Any chance someone of rank and wealth will take notice of my little sister? Anyway, may your mead stay cold and flow freely!"
"\n"
"\n— Gabbi Forestborne"
msgstr "친애하는 사촌 야킬드에게,"
"\n"
"\n네 남편은 어떠니? 아직 너에게 잘 대해주니? 그리고 그의 짜증나는 형제, 커쏘는? 분명 아직도 짜증나게 굴겠지! 그 곳의 툰드라 지역에는 어느 정도 네가 살 수 있을 만큼 나무가 자라니? 날씨는 어떻니, 그 곳도 윈드헬름과 같은 회색 하늘이니?"
"\n"
"\n네가 내 동생을 잘 대해줬으면 좋겠다. 너도 아그네더가 널 얼마나 의지하는지 잘 알잖니. 모든 사촌 중에서도 그녀는 널 가장 좋아했잖니.  또 그녀가 포레스터 훈련을 계속하도록 해 줘!"
"\n"
"\n괜찮은 재봉사는 찾았니? 네가 사는 곳 동쪽에 벌목 캠프가 있단다.  그 벌목꾼들 중 몇을 알고 있어. 좋은 사람들이야. 하지만 지난번에 적었던 이웃들에 관한 건 어떻니? 바로 왼쪽 집에 산다는 그 부자들은? 부유하고 지위가 높은 사람이 내 동생을 눈여겨 보는 일은 없겠지? 아무튼, 네 벌꿀주가 계속 차갑고 물처럼 흐르기를!"
"\n"
"\n— 가비 포레스트본"

#: 51188213-0-446
msgctxt "51188213-0-446"
msgid "Letter to Jakild"
msgstr "Jakild에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-445
msgctxt "21337012-0-445"
msgid "Agnedir,"
"\n"
"\nHow's life in the tundra with our cousins the Wood-Hewers? How's the quality of the trees? Are there enough of them to keep you busy? And what about your social life? Meet anyone special yet? Are there even any other people around Bonestrewn Crest, or is it just you and our cousins out there in the middle of nowhere?"
"\n"
"\nThings here in Windhelm have gotten strange since you left. Did you hear about Fildgor? Can you believe the Skald King's despicable brother has returned to Eastmarch? And with an army of renegade Nords and savage Orcs at his side? It's terrible."
"\n"
"\nAlvor sends his love. Tell Selgaard and Jakild that we're thinking about them. But not Kerthor. I'm still angry at him about what happened at last season's harvest festival. Him and those disgusting sour sweets! "
"\n"
"\nWrite soon!"
"\n—Gabbi"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-445
msgctxt "51188213-0-445"
msgid "Letter from Gabbi"
msgstr "가비에게 온 편지"

#: 21337012-0-4442
msgctxt "21337012-0-4442"
msgid "Atarga,"
"\n"
"\nWe shifted camp to the island just west of Vassamsi Grotto. Meet us there once you collect our fee. Rumor has it that this mine's worst than all the rest, so let's not linger here long, eh?"
"\n"
"\nIf you see those two half-wits in Sadrith Mora, give them a kick in the arse. We're running a smuggling outfit, not a gang of lazy drunks."
"\n"
"\nBothamul"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-4442
msgctxt "51188213-0-4442"
msgid "Bothamul's Orders"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-418
msgctxt "21337012-0-418"
msgid "Edhelfin,"
"\n"
"\nIf I never see your blighted face again, it will be too soon. Sal told me all about the "extra" shipments. And don't think I haven't noticed your finger on the scales in our dealings."
"\n"
"\nI'm giving you a warning as a courtesy. Sal likes you, and he'd mope for weeks if he saw you drawn and flayed. Next port we dock at, you've got one chance to jump ship. If I catch you, you're dead. If I see you before, during, or after, you're dead. Don't tempt me."
"\n"
"\nYour adoring sister,"
"\n"
"\nElandora"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-418
msgctxt "51188213-0-418"
msgid "Letter to Edhelfin"
msgstr "에델핀에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-3665
msgctxt "21337012-0-3665"
msgid "Concerning the one who calls himself a trader."
"\n"
"\nDobias has been stealing documents, contracts, and other financial records from the Gold Coast Trading Company. We have yet to determine what he plans to do with the stolen information, but profit probably plays a part in his plans. Is this reason enough to want him dead? Maybe."
"\n"
"\nCode Location: South of the Bank."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-3665
msgctxt "51188213-0-3665"
msgid "Soggy Note"
msgstr "물의 젖은 메모"

#: 21337012-0-343
msgctxt "21337012-0-343"
msgid "My Stalwart Sister,"
"\n"
"\nThe Three find you well, I hope. I have much to tell you. We've undertaken a full-scale irrigation project on the south side of town. One of the Argonians has shown us how to improve the ditch water system in place."
"\n"
"\nWe miss you here, Seyne. One person leaving a small town like ours leaves a big gap to fill!"
"\n"
"\nSeyne, know we think of you often. I'm so proud to be your brother. I know you're fighting for the safety of the Pact and that you're making Father proud at Vivec's side. Just remember, you always have a home here."
"\n"
"\nIf the campaign ends, rest easy knowing you still have a bunk."
"\n"
"\nFaithfully, "
"\n"
"\nSamel"
msgstr "내 충실한 여동생아,"
"\n"
"\n삼신들께서 널 살펴주시길 바란다. 할 말이 많구나. 우리는 마을 남쪽 방면에서 전면적인 관개 사업에 착수했단다. 아르고니안 한 명이 어떻게 배수 체계를 준비하는지 보여줬거든."
"\n"
"\n네가 여기 있던 때가 그립구나, 세인. 작은 마을에서 한 사람이 떠나면 채워야 할 큰 틈이 남는단다!"
"\n"
"\n세인, 우리가 널 자주 생각한다는 걸 알아두렴. 내가 네 오빠라서 자랑스럽구나. 나도 네가 조약의 안전을 위해 싸우고 있고 비벡에 계신 아버지를 자랑스럽게 하고 있다는 것을 안단다. 단지 항상 여기에 네 집이 있다는 사실만 기억하려무나."
"\n"
"\n작전이 끝나면 너를 위한 침상이 있다는 걸 알고 편히 있거라."
"\n"
"\n신의를 담아,"
"\n"
"\n사멜"

#: 51188213-0-343
msgctxt "51188213-0-343"
msgid "Letter to Seyne"
msgstr "세인에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-341
msgctxt "21337012-0-341"
msgid "Rana,"
"\n"
"\nI'm tired of the excuses. Yesterday's training exercise was shameful. When I was in charge, we never had these problems."
"\n"
"\nI think Rolunda would make a better soldier than some of these milk-drinkers!"
"\n"
"\nGet them together. The Pact is depending on us."
"\n"
"\n— Tillrani Snow-Bourne"
msgstr "라나,"
"\n"
"\n변명도 이젠 질렸어. 어제 훈련연습은 부끄러울 정도였다고. 내가 그 자리에 있었을 땐 한 번도 이런 문제가 없었단 말이야."
"\n"
"\n이 애송이 몇 놈들보다 롤룬다가 더 나은 병사가 되게 생겼어!"
"\n"
"\n녀석들을 집합시켜. 조약은 우리에게 기대고 있다고."
"\n"
"\n— 틸라니 스노우-보언"

#: 51188213-0-341
msgctxt "51188213-0-341"
msgid "Letter from Tillrani"
msgstr "틸라니로부터의 편지"

#: 21337012-0-302
msgctxt "21337012-0-302"
msgid "Dearest Dalii,"
"\n"
"\nWhile work in the mine is hard and barely worth the pay, I have good news! The foreman bribed a shepherd, and we now have kwama on site. There are plenty of eggs, so at least you know I'll be eating right."
"\n"
"\nI hope to see you soon,"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-302
msgctxt "51188213-0-302"
msgid "Incomplete Letter"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-3010
msgctxt "21337012-0-3010"
msgid "Cousin,"
"\n"
"\nYou said you were coming here for the cause. To respect what came before. To stop the piles of dung heaped upon us by interlopers."
"\n"
"\nBut the only interloper dung pile I've seen these past few months is your own. You eat my food and drink my rotmeth—all my rotmeth, all day long. At least your wife helps with the sweeping, but it's all after the messes you cause. Pull your weight or start paying rent."
"\n"
"\n—Glardel"
"\n"
"\nPS: I've seen what they wear in Malabal Tor. "Too lazy to wash your own clothes" is not "Malabal Tor style." Put a shirt on—you're walking Altmer propaganda."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-3010
msgctxt "51188213-0-3010"
msgid "Letter to Negaelion"
msgstr "네겔리온에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-2991
msgctxt "21337012-0-2991"
msgid "Stelvene! Come back, you fool. He yet lives!"
"\n"
"\nI can take you to him. We have a wagon! Your father has an entire legion looking for you. How much of your fortune have you spent hidden away for this long?"
"\n"
"\nCome home, and I will tell you everything I know."
"\n"
"\nAbandon this madness. Abandon this false god!"
"\n"
"\n—Rincous"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2991
msgctxt "51188213-0-2991"
msgid "Letter to Stelvene Lothaire"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2985
msgctxt "21337012-0-2985"
msgid "Your Royal Majesty High King Emeric,"
"\n"
"\nThough I am certain you receive many correspondences from the nobility, it is my hope you will give this missive the attention it deserves."
"\n"
"\nI write to you not only as a downtrodden member of the court, but as an advocate for every man and woman (those of sufficient nobility to be worth noting, at least) who has been slighted and ostracized for no good reason. It is my firm belief that, no matter your family history or how many cats you care for or what special … dietary restrictions you might have, all nobles have the right by birth to inclusion in the court and related gatherings."
"\n"
"\nFor no other reason than sheer prejudice, I have been repeatedly ignored, overlooked, and rejected by those who are my peers. This is a great injustice and it cannot be allowed to continue! My blood is just as good as any other noble's, and I demand to be given the respect I deserve."
"\n"
"\nOnly you can truly command the court, and so you are my only chance for redemption. Please, my King, I beg of you to publicly denounce this treatment so that I might regain the standing I deserve."
"\n"
"\nYour Loyal Subject,"
"\nAdelil"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2985
msgctxt "51188213-0-2985"
msgid "High King Emeric, I Implore You!"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2984
msgctxt "21337012-0-2984"
msgid "Dearest Finia,"
"\n"
"\nYou've no idea how long I debated sending this letter, but in the end I fear I must do what is best for myself and my esteemed relations. You have been a valuable friend and ally at court for many years, which makes me all the more shocked by the word I've received—from several reputable sources, I might add—about your recent political … "activities.""
"\n"
"\nIt is with a heavy heart and great regret that I inform you that I no longer wish to be associated with you in any way. Advocating the ideals you apparently stand for during a time of war and consorting with the company you have been spotted with is nothing short of treason, and I will not be associated with any of it."
"\n"
"\nIt is my hope that you may yet see the folly of your ways before it ruins you. Do not write back."
"\n"
"\n—Duchess Olivie Delrusc"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2984
msgctxt "51188213-0-2984"
msgid "Letter to Finia Marcott"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2982
msgctxt "21337012-0-2982"
msgid "Dear Applicant,"
"\n"
"\nWe at the Stormhaven Bluster regret to inform you that we must reject your recent submission for an advertisement in our widely-distributed broadsheet. Though we respect your desire to promote your organization, we took issue with some of your word choices and felt they were not appropriate for our audience."
"\n"
"\nThe headlines "GOLD FOR BLOOD" and "START A CAREER IN KILLING" were simply too extreme for our pages. Additionally, the appeal to individuals who "take any job and don't ask questions" might compromise our reputation as an upstanding publication."
"\n"
"\nWe are happy to either return your fee or accept a new submission that is more appropriate. Please see our recent edition's notice from The Iron Heels, another group similar to your mercenary organization, for an example of the kind of promotions with which we are more comfortable."
"\n"
"\nRegards,"
"\nThe Stormhaven Bluster Editorial Staff"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2982
msgctxt "51188213-0-2982"
msgid "Stormhaven Bluster Rejection Notice"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2936
msgctxt "21337012-0-2936"
msgid "Wyress Gwen,"
"\n"
"\nThings have gotten strange around the Wyrd Tree since you've been traveling. Remember those weird vines that began sprouting a few weeks ago? Well, they've grown huge and they seem … evil … somehow. I know it sounds crazy, but that's the only way I can describe it. Evil with a capital "E.""
"\n"
"\nI noticed that the forest animals have become agitated and even aggressive when they get close to the strange vines. Moreover, as the vines grow stronger, the aggressive behavior lasts longer. I'm beginning to fear that the creatures will attack soon. That's how much the presence of the vines has changed them."
"\n"
"\nAnd now it's worse than I feared. Some of the vines have mutated, and now they spawn lurchers from their corrupted thorns. "
"\n"
"\nI'm sorry, Wyress, but I can't stay here any longer. Bloodthorn cultists have attacked us and taken control of the portal stone caves beneath our huts. I can't prove it, but I'm certain these cultists are responsible for our recent troubles. I have failed you, but I hope you can forgive me. I know you won't listen, but I urge you to stay away from the Wyrd Tree until this all blows over."
"\n"
"\nWyress Domi"
msgstr "위어리스 그웬에게"
"\n"
"\n네가 여행을 떠나고 나서 월드 거대수 주변에는 이상한 일들이 벌어지고 있어. 몇 주 전에 생기기 시작한 저 이상한 덩굴을 기억하고 있지? 그게 점점 커져서, 뭐라 해야 할까... 사악한 것으로 변하고 있는 것 같아. 믿기지 않을지도 모르지만 그렇게밖에 말할 수가 없어. 저건 분명 사악한 존재일거야."
"\n"
"\n숲의 동물들은 덩굴에 다가가면 흥분하고 공격적으로 변해. 그게 덩굴이 성장함에 따라 동물들이 공격적으로 변하는 시간도 점점 짧아지는 것 같아. 누군가가 여길 습격하는 것은 이젠 시간문제겠지. 덩굴이 동물들을 바꿔놓았어."
"\n"
"\n상황이 점점 악화되었어. 덩굴 일부가 자연변이를 일으켜, 사악한 가시들이 러쳐를 만들어 내고 있어."
"\n"
"\n위어리스에겐 미안하지만, 이제 더 이상 여기에 있을수가 없어. 블러드 쏜의 신자들이 공격해서, 오두막 아래에 있는 포탈 스톤이 있는 동굴까지 점령해버렸어. 증명은 할 수 없지만, 최근 일어난 문제 원인은 분명 저 신자들일거야. 실망시켜서 미안해. 하지만 용서해줘. 이 사건이 정리될 때까지 월드 거대수에는 절대 가까이 다가가지 않도록 해."
"\n"
"\n위어리스 도미로부터"

#: 51188213-0-2936
msgctxt "51188213-0-2936"
msgid "Letter to Wyress Gwen"
msgstr "위어리스 그웬에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-2783
msgctxt "21337012-0-2783"
msgid "Geldrion,"
"\n"
"\nNext time, don't hide your gold in a stupid barrel. Any old fool could come along and take it. I took your gold to the bank for safekeeping. That's what banks are for, you know. Didn't mother teach you anything? "
"\n"
"\nI didn't want to lug the shield along, too, but it's not like anyone but you is going to use that old thing. As for your onion, well, stashing that in the bank is just plain silly. And it's starting to smell."
"\n"
"\nYour brother,"
"\nRandolph"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2783
msgctxt "51188213-0-2783"
msgid "Letter to Geldrion"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2549
msgctxt "21337012-0-2549"
msgid "Ofglog gro-Barkbite,"
"\n"
"\nThe entire stronghold gathered around to see what you learned at that fancy college. We closed our eyes, just like you asked. You said some fancy words, and then … nothing. When we opened our eyes, you were gone."
"\n"
"\nMoramat opened her fool mouth and wondered if you'd turned invisible—and they all looked at me! Everyone knows you've been sniffing around my forge for years, and they know I've turned you away. Then Sharnag blurted out, "Looks like he finally came to his senses," and they all started laughing."
"\n"
"\nThis is the last time you make a fool of me. Wherever you went, I hope you never come back. I hate you."
"\n"
"\n—Shakul"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2549
msgctxt "51188213-0-2549"
msgid "Letter to Ofglog"
msgstr "오프글로그에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-2548
msgctxt "21337012-0-2548"
msgid "<<1>>,"
"\n"
"\nI know you're busy, big brother, but I still haven't received the shipment you promised me! Please send my order as soon as you can or we'll have nothing to sell at the family shop."
"\n"
"\nAnyway, I can't wait until I get up to Mournhold. I want to see this wonderful forge you wrote us about. And I can't wait to meet all of the crafters and smiths that work for you!"
"\n"
"\nAll my love, dear brother!"
"\n"
"\n—Blivisi"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2548
msgctxt "51188213-0-2548"
msgid "Letter to Artisans Craftworks"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2543
msgctxt "21337012-0-2543"
msgid "Dear Laenira,"
"\n"
"\nEverything is as you instructed. Beware the wisps! They look like flowers, and I've had several close calls."
"\n"
"\nSee you soon, love."
msgstr "사랑하는 라에니라에게,"
"\n"
"\n전부 당신이 말한 대로 해 놨어. 위습을 조심해! 마치 꽃처럼 생겼는데, 몇 번인가 구사일생으로 살아났다니까."
"\n"
"\n곧 만나자, 내 사랑."

#: 51188213-0-2543
msgctxt "51188213-0-2543"
msgid "Letter to Laenira"
msgstr "라에니라에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-2537
msgctxt "21337012-0-2537"
msgid "Fellow knights, no matter what Duke Nathaniel plots, we cannot betray our oath. Only if he moves openly will we move against him. If you stand with me, listen for the horn. "
"\n"
"\n-Sir Edmund"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2537
msgctxt "51188213-0-2537"
msgid "Sir Edmund's Letter"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2534
msgctxt "21337012-0-2534"
msgid "Our scouts report the weakest giant encampment lies Northwest of Riften in an area commonly known as Autumnshade. Go there, slay the giants, and raise them to fight for us. I know their size makes giants unusually hard to raise, but you will try until you succeed. Sinmur needs an army to lead. "
"\n"
"\nThallik Wormfather"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2534
msgctxt "51188213-0-2534"
msgid "Thallik's Orders"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2532
msgctxt "21337012-0-2532"
msgid "Strastnoc,"
"\n"
"\nYou're probably resting your hairy arse on the throne of Evermore by now. I wish we were having as much luck. I know this deal with the Worms is important, but I'm starting to wonder whether we can really trust them. I'll explain more when you get back."
"\n"
"\nLinele"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2532
msgctxt "51188213-0-2532"
msgid "Letter to Strastnoc"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2522
msgctxt "21337012-0-2522"
msgid "Ah, fair Cynhamoth, how you flatter me with tempting gifts!"
"\n"
"\nYou know I'm watching my waistline, but still you send me buttered scamp knuckles."
"\n"
"\n(They were delicious, by the way!)"
"\n"
"\n—Sir Cadwell"
msgstr "아, 어여쁜 신하모스, 매력적인 선물로 나에게 잘 보이려 하다니!"
"\n"
"\n내가 허리둘레를 신경쓴단 걸 알면서도 버터를 바른 스캠프 무릎살을 보내다니 말이오."
"\n"
"\n(그나저나, 스캠프가 맛있더구려!)"
"\n"
"\n— 캐드웰 경"

#: 51188213-0-2522
msgctxt "51188213-0-2522"
msgid "Letter to Cynhamoth"
msgstr "신하모스에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-2520
msgctxt "21337012-0-2520"
msgid "The feud continues, you miserable bucket of bolts!"
"\n"
"\nYou insult me, Zemarek—and that I cannot forgive!"
"\n"
"\nLunch again on Middas?"
"\n"
"\n—Sir Cadwell"
msgstr "불화가 계속되는구나, 이 고약한 볼트 더미야!"
"\n"
"\n그대는 날 모욕했다, 제마렉. 그리고 그러한 행위는 용서할 수 없다!"
"\n"
"\n미다스에 다시 점심이나 하겠나?"
"\n"
"\n—캐드웰 경"

#: 51188213-0-2520
msgctxt "51188213-0-2520"
msgid "Letter to Zemarek-Thul"
msgstr "제마렉-툴에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-2498
msgctxt "21337012-0-2498"
msgid "Dearest Seron,"
"\n"
"\nI fear the plague has found me. I shall miss you, my love."
"\n"
"\n—Ida"
msgstr "친애하는 세론에게,"
"\n"
"\n내가 전염병에 걸린게 아닐까 두려워. 네가 그리울거야, 내사랑."
"\n"
"\n-아이다"

#: 51188213-0-2498
msgctxt "51188213-0-2498"
msgid "Letter to Narsis"
msgstr "나르시스에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-2496
msgctxt "21337012-0-2496"
msgid "My dear Manivol,"
"\n"
"\nHouse Dres' support of my Maulborn initiative warms my heart. And your generous contributions of gold and resources assure our success. "
"\n"
"\nThe Three will be revealed as the false gods they are and Morrowind will be free!"
"\n"
"\n—Vox"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2496
msgctxt "51188213-0-2496"
msgid "Letter from Magistrix Vox"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2494
msgctxt "21337012-0-2494"
msgid "Comrade, I trust your judgement. "
"\n"
"\nThe find of this "Earth Forge" is a boon, and one we should keep in trust. Any dogs who wish to benefit from your cunning will have to spill guild blood to find the place."
"\n"
"\nYour request to establish a permanent presence in the mountains is approved. Our master craftsmen will want to try their hand with that infernal construct at the heart of the mountain."
"\n"
"\nMake sure their other kit is moved out there as well. Perhaps our carvers and tailors will benefit from the fresh air, eh? "
"\n"
"\n- Jofnir Iceblade, Guildmaster"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2494
msgctxt "51188213-0-2494"
msgid "From Jofnir to Merric"
msgstr "요프니어가 메릭에게"

#: 21337012-0-2474
msgctxt "21337012-0-2474"
msgid "Master Avayan,"
"\n"
"\nThis one will be visiting Selfora shortly and would love to make use of your fabulous crafting stations— provided you're amenable. I'll even bring a few bottles of golden wine to refill your pantry!"
"\n"
"\n—Magister Marashi"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2474
msgctxt "51188213-0-2474"
msgid "Letter to the Twilight Mage"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2472
msgctxt "21337012-0-2472"
msgid "Danier,"
"\n"
"\nOur shop's outside Wayrest (to avoid city taxes). I hope they won't find us."
"\n"
"\nGo to Sentinel, where it's safe."
"\n"
"\n—Matilde"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2472
msgctxt "51188213-0-2472"
msgid "Letter to Danier"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2471
msgctxt "21337012-0-2471"
msgid "Captain Kordella,"
"\n"
"\nYou must be aware of my father's campaign to reclaim the Crown of Shornhelm. Soon, all of Rivenspire shall bow to House Montclair."
"\n	"
"\nNow for my offer. Pledge your forces to me and help us topple the houses of Dorell and Tamrith, or on my mother's grave I shall see the Bitterhands destroyed."
"\n"
"\nIn other matters, how's that fetching maiden of yours? If I recall, she had an adorable mole just above her luscious lips. Perhaps I could borrow her. As a gesture of good faith."
"\n"
"\nI look forward to your timely response."
"\n"
"\n—LLM"
msgstr ""

