#: 21337012-0-2219
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "21337012-0-2219"
msgid "Alma,"
"\n"
"\nStay strong on the Shadowed Path, my heart. Perform your duties for our lord and obey my orders. For now, this is your lot. You must not rise too swiftly in our ranks, or favoritism will be cried out by the others. Volcatia especially is watchful, slit-eyed with suspicion and jealousy."
"\n"
"\nCurb your impatience and your tongue. They will be the death of us both otherwise. To keep you from indiscretion, I command you to journey to the ancient ruins of Nagastani. Think of this as an opportunity, not a banishment. Rout or corrupt any who reside there. Use the ancient evil that still permeates that ground, build your strength, and await my signal. Soon Blue Road Keep will be ours, under your heel."
"\n"
"\nThe Diabolist rank you crave will be but a stepping stone to the power you can achieve under me. Together, we will crush all of Cyrodiil!"
"\n"
"\n— Dreadlord Naucratius"
msgstr "앨마,"
"\n"
"\n암흑의 길에 강하게 머물러 라. 내 마음. 우리 주인님의 임무를 수행하고 내 명령에 복종하십시오. 당분간 이것은 당신의 많은 것입니다. 당신은 우리 계급에서 너무 빨리 일어나서는 안됩니다. 그렇지 않으면 편애가 다른 사람들에 의해 부르짖습니다. Volcatia는 특히 조심스럽고 의심스럽고 질투하는 눈이 많이 내립니다."
"\n"
"\n불편 함과 혀를 식히십시오. 그들은 둘 다 그렇지 않으면 죽음이 될 것입니다. 당신을 무분별하게하기 위해 나는 당신에게 Nagastani의 고대 유적지를 여행하라고 명령합니다. 이것을 기회라고 생각하십시오. 추방이 아닙니다. 거기에 거주하는 사람을 훼손하거나 부패시킵니다. 여전히 그 땅에 스며 들고 힘을 얻고 내 신호를 기다리고있는 고대 악을 사용하십시오. 곧 Blue Road Keep은 당신의 발 뒤꿈치 밑에서 우리의 것입니다."
"\n"
"\n당신이 갈망하는 Diabolist 순위는 나 밑에서 얻을 수있는 힘의 디딤돌이 될 것입니다. 함께, 우리는 모든 Cyrodiil을 분쇄 할 것입니다!"
"\n"
"\nDreadlord Naucratius-G-"

#: 51188213-0-2219
msgctxt "51188213-0-2219"
msgid "Letter to Alma"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2182
msgctxt "21337012-0-2182"
msgid "My Dear Marina,"
"\n"
"\nA rumor has come to me; I hope you can disprove it. I hear that Octavimus is planning to leave, to run from his obligations. We both know what a mistake that would be. You need to talk him out of it."
"\n"
"\nI say this for your health and for his. We both know what will happen if Octavimus leaves. And how could you think of leaving all your friends and the life of the city? I can't believe you would do that."
"\n"
"\nDon't force my hand here, Marina. It won't be pleasant for anyone. So be a good wife and see that Octavimus stays put."
"\n"
"\n— Niro"
msgstr "친애하는 마리나,"
"\n"
"\n내 귀에 소문이 들려오고 있소. 그게 헛소문임을 당신이 증명해준다면 좋겠군. 옥타비무스가 자기 의무를 버려두고 떠날 계획을 세우고 있다고 하오. 우리 둘 다 그게 큰 실수가 될 것임을 알잖소. 옥타비무스한테 말해서 그만두게 해야 하오."
"\n"
"\n당신과 그의 안전을 위해서 하는 말이라오. 우리 둘다 옥타비무스가 떠나면 생길 일을 알잖소. 그리고 어떻게 당신이 친구들과 도시 생활을 떠날 수가 있단 말이오? 당신이 그러리라고는 믿을 수가 없소."
"\n"
"\n여기서 내 힘을 행사하게 만들지 말아 주시오, 마리나. 누구에게도 좋은 일은 아닐 것이오. 좋은 아내가 되어서 옥타비무스가 그대로 머무르게 해 주길 바라겠소."
"\n"
"\n— 니로"

#: 51188213-0-2182
msgctxt "51188213-0-2182"
msgid "Letter to Marina"
msgstr "마리나에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-2145
msgctxt "21337012-0-2145"
msgid "Dear Sir,"
"\n"
"\nI know you prefer to remain anonymous, but I must write to express my thanks. Your tireless work over the last several years to help the Orsinium Orphanage has been beyond generous. The gold and gifts you sent have been put to good use, warming the beds and the hearts of countless Orc children. We have also been able to expand the orphanage itself, making it the finest in all the Daggerfall Covenant. "
"\n"
"\nOur city's scholars were shocked to see the tomes of Orcish history you tracked down on our behalf. You have restored knowledge to our people that was believed lost for all time. May Mauloch bless you for what you've done."
"\n"
"\nOorga gra-Shazgul"
"\n"
"\nHeadmistress, Orsinium Home for Displaced Children"
msgstr "친애하는 귀하,"
"\n"
"\n당신이 익명으로 남아 있길 선호한다는 걸 알고 있지만, 감사를 표현하기 위해 이 편지를 써야 했습니다. 지난 몇 년 동안 오시니움 고아원을 끊임 없이 도와 주셔서 정말 감사합니다. 당신이 보내주신 돈과 선물은 침대와 셀 수 없는 오크 아이들의 심장을 덮히며 좋은 곳에 쓰였습니다. 저희는 또한 고아원을 확장할 수 있었고, 대거폴 동맹에서 가장 좋은 고아원이 되었지요."
"\n"
"\n오시니움의 학자들은 저희를 위해 당신이 찾아 주신 오크 역사서들을 보고 충격에 빠졌습니다. 당신은 영원히 잃어버렸다고 생각했던 우리 사람들에게 지식을 되찾아 주셨어요. 마울록이 당신을 축복하기를."
"\n"
"\n울가 그라-샤즈굴"
"\n"
"\n난민 아이들을 위한 오시니움 집의 교장"

#: 51188213-0-2145
msgctxt "51188213-0-2145"
msgid "Letter from the Orsinium Orphanage"
msgstr "오시니움 고아원에서 온 편지"

#: 21337012-0-2133
msgctxt "21337012-0-2133"
msgid "Calahawn,"
"\n"
"\nI must firmly decline the invitation to join your magical misadventure."
"\n"
"\nAppealing to Hircine to aid you against "all the Dominion" is insanity, not to mention gross overreaction. It's always dangerous to nudge the shoulder of a Daedric Prince. Why further doom yourself by relying upon a patchwork band of sorcerous fools?"
"\n"
"\nI don't know if that lot has the skill to find their way to the nearest Mages Guild chapter, let alone appeal to a Daedric Prince! But I suppose you need them. No sane Elf would aid you. I won't, certainly. I'm as staunch a follower of the Green Pact as you, but where you go I cannot follow."
"\n"
"\nYou must think. The Dominion is the only chance to survive this war! You want to hunt our allies as our real enemies prepare to burn Valenwood to ash."
"\n"
"\nI refuse to sign my name to this. I want no justiciar finding this on your body and thinking I had anything to do with your madness."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2133
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "51188213-0-2133"
msgid "Letter to Calahawn"
msgstr "칼라완의 편지"

#: 21337012-0-2126
msgctxt "21337012-0-2126"
msgid "Turenn,"
"\n"
"\nAfter so many years of lying low, I thought they had forgotten about me, but it seems that's not the case. The Ring of Daggers is still after me and they're closing in. One of their agents is asking questions around Moira's Hope and I need to escape. "
"\n"
"\nIn the short term, I am prepared. I have a hideout within the central crypt of the Sanguine Barrows. I can seal myself within and survive for some time, but I need you to come as soon as possible. I am hoping you can help me relocate and assume a new identity once again. "
"\n"
"\nP.S.: Watch out for the trolls!"
"\n"
"\n— Gerard Althen"
msgstr "투렌,"
"\n"
"\n오랫동안 바짝 엎드려 살았으니, 난 그들이 나를 잊었을 거라고 생각했다네. 하지만 그런 것 같지 않아. 대거단은 여전히 나를 찾고 있고, 내게 가까워지고 있다네. 그들 요원 중 한 명이 모이라의 호프 근처에서 나에 대해 물었고, 난 탈출해야만 하네."
"\n"
"\n나는 단기적으로는 준비가 되어 있다네. 생귄 고분의 중앙 납골당에 내 은신처가 있어. 나는 문을 걸어 잠그고 얼마 간 살아갈 수 있지만, 최대한 빨리 자네가 와 줬으면 좋겠네. 내가 장소를 옮겨 다시 한번 새 위조 신분을 얻을 수 있게 도와주게나."
"\n"
"\n추신 : 트롤들을 조심하게!"
"\n"
"\n— 제랄드 알텐"

#: 51188213-0-2126
msgctxt "51188213-0-2126"
msgid "Letter from Althen"
msgstr "알텐에게서 온 편지"

#: 21337012-0-2067
msgctxt "21337012-0-2067"
msgid "To whoever finds this,"
"\n"
"\nLeave this place. It is cursed. There are too many of them, now."
"\n"
"\nFirst it was just one. He hid in the mine and seduced our children. Now they have joined him. "
"\n"
"\nThere are only a few of us left, but they are everywhere. "
"\n"
"\nWe can't leave. We won't survive. But we refuse to surrender."
"\n"
"\nBetter to be torn limb from limb than to become one of them."
msgstr "누구든지 이걸 찾는 사람에게,"
"\n"
"\n이곳을 떠나라. 여기는 저주받았다. 지금은 놈들이 너무나도 많다."
"\n"
"\n처음에는 단 하나였다. 놈은 광산 속에 숨어 우리 아이들을 유혹했다. 이제 아이들은 놈들과 함께한다."
"\n"
"\n우리는 몇 남지 않았지만, 놈들은 온 사방에 있다."
"\n"
"\n우리는 떠날 수 없다. 우리는 살아남지 못할 것이다. 하지만 항복하지도 않을 것이다."
"\n"
"\n놈들의 일원이 되느니 사지가 갈가리 찢겨지는 편이 더 낫다."

#: 51188213-0-2067
msgctxt "51188213-0-2067"
msgid "Leave This Place"
msgstr "이곳을 떠나라"

#: 21337012-0-2035
msgctxt "21337012-0-2035"
msgid "Herminius Sophus,"
"\n"
"\nDespite the many times which I have written to you to advise you against this tour of the historical sites of Hammerfell, I have received notification that your ship leaves within the month. I strongly encourage you to reconsider this trip and stay with your dear sister Lepida in Reaper's March instead."
"\n"
"\nWith that said, if my urging does not sway you, think instead of the scholars who have gone missing at Makela Leki's final resting place in the Sunken Road."
"\n"
"\nAminyas for one, a High Elf mage of no small talent. I suspect he was there digging for information which might rekindle old grievances within the Daggerfall Covenant, as he went on his expedition shortly after the Covenant was formed."
"\n"
"\nBefore him there was the late Morgaulle Dechery of Evermore who, generations ago, disappeared while writing a piece about King Joile's actions shortly after the incident occurred. The manuscript she was writing was doubtless the sort of political jockeying or apologist tripe which one expects from the period, but her death was still regrettable."
"\n"
"\nFor your sister's sake, do not make me have to add your name to this list."
"\n"
"\n— J. Ithaka"
msgstr "헤르미니우스 소퍼스,"
"\n"
"\n해머펠의 사적지로 가는 이 여행에 대해 수없이 서면으로 조언을 했건만, 한 달 안에 네 배가 떠난다는 통지가 오더구나. 난 네가 이 여행을 재고하고 대신 리퍼스 마치에 있는 네 소중한 여동생 레피다와 함께 지내는 것을 강력하게 추천하겠다."
"\n"
"\n그러한 의미에서, 내 재촉이 너에게 별 감흥이 없다면 파묻힌 길에 있는 마켈라 레키의 마지막 안식처에서 실종된 학자들을 생각해 보거라. "
"\n"
"\n우선 작지 않은 재능을 가졌던 하이엘프 마법사 아미냐스가 있지. 난 그가 거기서 대거폴 동맹의 오래된 불쟁을 다시 불러일으킬 수도 있는 정보를 탐구하고 있었다고 생각한단다. 동맹이 형성된 직후에 여행을 떠났기 때문이지."
"\n"
"\n아미냐스 이전에는 수세기 전 사건이 일어난 직후에 졸리 왕의 행동에 대한 글을 쓰다가 실종된 에버모어의 모르갈 데셔리가 있었지. 그녀가 쓴 원고는 의심의 여지 없이 그 시대의 정치적인 속임수 또는 시시한 선전물이었겠지만, 그녀의 죽음은 여전히 유감스러운 일이란다."
"\n"
"\n네 여동생을 위해서라도 이 명단에 네 이름을 추가하게 하지 말거라."
"\n"
"\n— J. Ithaka"

#: 51188213-0-2035
msgctxt "51188213-0-2035"
msgid "Letter to Herminius Sophus"
msgstr "헤르미니우스 소퍼스에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1962
msgctxt "21337012-0-1962"
msgid "Confidential Diplomatic Missive: Thalmor Eyes Only"
"\n"
"\nDeliver Only To: Aicantar, Sapiarch of Indoctrination, Crystal Tower, Alinor"
"\n"
"\nYour Sapience, "
"\n"
"\nIn retrospect, I am of the opinion that titling a para-military unit the "Fists of Thalmor" has been an error of nomenclature. Though accurate as to the function of said unit, in the local vernacular the title has been shortened to simply "Thalmor," which inaccurately conflates our diplomatic corps with the Dominion military. Furthermore, inasmuch as the Fists, in pursuit of their enforcement duties, may occasionally exert more force than some might think necessary, this taints the Thalmor with a perception that our agents are heavy-handed thugs. Needless to say, this doesn't help when negotiating for aid from the local indigenes. "
"\n"
"\nIn future, I think we would be wise to return to referring to our enforcement units as "Justiciars," even if it does make our Khajiiti citizens disinclined to join because it sounds so stuffy. "
"\n"
"\nYours in Diplomacy, "
"\n"
"\nCanonreeve Falduil"
msgstr "기밀 외교 서한: 탈모어 요원만 열람할 것"
"\n"
"\n알리노어 수정탑의 교화의 사피악, 아이칸타에게만 전달할 것"
"\n"
"\n지혜로운 분이시여,"
"\n"
"\n돌이켜보면, 준군사조직에 "탈모어의 주먹"이라는 명칭을 붙인 것은 그 명명법에 오류가 있었지 않았나 합니다. 조직의 역할을 정확하게 표현해주는 명칭이기는 하지만, 현지 토착어에서는 그 명칭이 단순히 "탈모어"로 줄여지는 현상이 발생하여 저희 외교 단체를 자치령 군사 조직과 잘못 연결되게 하고 있습니다. 게다가 탈모어의 주먹이 집행 임무를 수행하고 있으며 이따금 필요하다고 생각되는 것 이상의 무력을 행사할 가능성이 있다는 점을 고려해본다면, 저희 요원들이 포악한 폭력배들인 것처럼 인식되게 하여 탈모어의 이름을 더럽힐 가능성도 존재합니다. 말할 필요도 없겠지만, 이는 원주민들의 도움을 얻어내는데 도움이 되지 않습니다."
"\n"
"\n앞으로는 저희 집행 부대의 명칭을 다시 "사법관"으로 되돌리는 것이 현명할 것이라고 생각합니다. 저희 카짓 시민들이 듣기에는 너무 격식적인 것으로 들려서 조직에 가입하기를 꺼려한다 해도 말입니다."
"\n"
"\n평안한 외교가 있기를,"
"\n"
"\n규범행정관 팔두일"

#: 51188213-0-1962
msgctxt "51188213-0-1962"
msgid "Regarding the "Fists of Thalmor""
msgstr ""탈모어의 주먹"에 대하여"

#: 21337012-0-1941
msgctxt "21337012-0-1941"
msgid "Scholar Oppius,"
"\n"
"\nOnce again you repeat your assertions that Goblins have domesticated creatures of several species, including spiders and kwama. And once again I must inform you that the academy's journal will publish no papers making such outlandish claims without conclusive proof."
"\n"
"\nYou offer no proof for the excellent reason that none exists. Goblins are not intelligent enough to be domesticated themselves, let alone to domesticate other species. Your premise is ridiculous, your reasoning is flimsy, and your conclusions are insupportable."
"\n"
"\nThe more unlikely one's thesis, the stronger one's proof must be to overcome disbelief. Offering no proof for an assertion as controversial as yours invites ridicule. And I am delighted to provide it."
"\n"
"\nDo not waste my time with any further submissions except in the improbable event that you obtain conclusive proof of your claims. Even then, a witness credible to the academy must swear to the veracity of your paper and must be willing to co-author it."
"\n"
"\nI do not expect to hear from you again. I wish you the best of luck in your future endeavors as a charlatan."
"\n"
"\nFelicitas Mallicius"
"\nEditor-in-Chief"
"\nSpecies and Speculation Journal"
msgstr "학자 오피우스,"
"\n"
"\n고블린들이 거미와 크와마를 포함한 몇몇 종들을 길들였다는 주장을 또 다시 반복하더군. 그리고 난 결정적인 증거 없이는 그런 기이한 주장을 학술원 학술지에 실어줄 수 없다는 사실을 또 다시 알려줘야 하고 말이다."
"\n"
"\n넌 존재했던 적이 없는 현상에 대한 훌륭한 증거를 단 하나도 제출하지 않았어. 고블린은 다른 종을 길들이기는 고사하고 자신들을 길들일 지능조차 가지지 못한 존재들이다. 너의 전제는 터무니없고, 너의 추론은 조잡하며, 너의 결론은 참고 봐 줄 수가 없단 말이다."
"\n"
"\n더 믿기 힘든 논문일수록 그 불신을 극복하기 위해 더 강력한 증거가 필요한 법이다. 그렇게 논란이 많은 주장에 대한 증거도 제출하지 않으면 조롱만 유발할 뿐이야. 그리고 난 그 사실을 증명할 수 있어 아주 기쁘다."
"\n"
"\n네 주장에 대한 결정적인 증거를 얻어낸다는 말도 안 되는 상황이 일어나지 않는 이상 내 시간을 더는 낭비하지 마라. 만약에 그런 일이 일어난다 한들, 신용할 수 있는 증인이 학술원에서 네 논문이 가진 진실성에 대한 맹세를 해야 하고, 증인에게 그 논문의 공동 저자로 기록되겠다는 용의가 있어야만 한다."
"\n"
"\n너에게서 더 이상의 소식이 들려오리라 기대하지는 않는다. 미래에는 네가 사기꾼으로서 최선을 다한다면 좋겠군."
"\n"
"\n펠리시타스 말리시우스"
"\n편집장"
"\n종의 고찰 학술지"

#: 51188213-0-1941
msgctxt "51188213-0-1941"
msgid "Academy's Rejection Letter"
msgstr "학술원의 거절 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1940
msgctxt "21337012-0-1940"
msgid "Evrien,"
"\n"
"\nYou soulless, gold-gouging son of a horker! When I see you next, surround yourself with bodyguards or I'll strangle you and let the Bloody Hands feast on your remains."
"\n"
"\nTripling your transport fees is outrageous. Our present need forces me to pay, as you well know. But when order is restored to Cyrodiil, I'll take these ill-gotten gains out of your hide."
"\n"
"\nI don't know whether to hope you make it here safely or that the Goblins kill you. Either would give me satisfaction."
"\n"
"\n— Ufgra gra-Gum"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1940
msgctxt "51188213-0-1940"
msgid "Letter to Evrien"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1939
msgctxt "21337012-0-1939"
msgid "Raelynne,"
"\n"
"\nOur master's commands part us for now, but we will be together forever. Raise an army in Underpall, and I will raise mine in Lipsand. We will meet in the Twilight Woods and sweep all of northern Cyrodiil before us. "
"\n"
"\nAnd who knows how long the master will lead? There are many casualties in war, even among the mighty and seemingly immortal. Perhaps we will soon be our own masters once again, as we were in Wayrest."
"\n"
"\nI long to be with you again, sweet sister."
"\n"
"\n— Gaston"
msgstr "렐린,"
"\n"
"\n지금은 우리 주인의 명령 때문에 서로 떨어져 있지만, 우린 영원히 함께야. 언더팔에서 네 군대를 일으켜. 난 립산드에서 내 군대를 일으킬 테니까. 황혼의 숲에서 만난 다음에 우리 앞에 놓인 북부 시로딜을 전부 쓸어 버리자."
"\n"
"\n그리고 주인이 그 자리에 얼마나 오래 있을지 누가 알겠어? 전쟁에서는 사상자가 많이 나오는 법이야. 심지어는 강대하고 무적인 것 처럼 보이는 자들 중에서도 말이야. 어쩌면 다시 한번 우리가 우리 스스로의 주인이 될 수 있을지도 몰라. 웨이레스트에서 그랬던 것 처럼 말이야."
"\n"
"\n다시 너와 함께 있고 싶은 생각이 간절하구나, 귀여운 여동생아."
"\n"
"\n— 가스톤"

#: 51188213-0-1939
msgctxt "51188213-0-1939"
msgid "Letter to Raelynne"
msgstr "렐린에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1927
msgctxt "21337012-0-1927"
msgid "Though you were not born under the sign of the Shadow, it does not mean Sithis or the Night Mother ignores your pleas. Pray to them and you shall gain power. Kill in their name, and they will respect you. Stand up for the heritage of our people."
"\n"
"\nDo not be swayed by Uta-Tei and her followers. Practicing the Wood Elf religion is heresy! She cannot see that we will become slaves once again if we do not act. You were chosen as one of my hunters for a reason. We will fight together, we will die together!"
"\n"
"\n—Slim-Jah"
msgstr "그대가 그림자의 표식 아래서 태어나지 않았더라도, 그것이 시디스나 밤의 어머니께서 그대의 기도를 무시한다는 뜻은 아니다. 그분들께 기도하면 힘을 얻을 것이다. 그분들의 이름으로 죽이면 그분들의 경의를 받으리라. 우리 민족의 유산을 위해 일어나라."
"\n"
"\n우타-테이와 그 추종자들에게 흔들리지 말라. 우드 엘프의 종교를 따르는 것은 이단이다! 우타-테이는 우리가 행동하지 않으면 다시 한번 노예가 될 것임을 알지 못한다. 그대가 내 사냥꾼으로 선택받은 것에는 그만한 이유가 있다. 우리는 함께 싸우고, 함께 죽을 것이다!"
"\n"
"\n—슬림-자"

#: 51188213-0-1927
msgctxt "51188213-0-1927"
msgid "The Night Mother Watches"
msgstr "밤의 어머니께서 지켜보신다"

#: 21337012-0-1912
msgctxt "21337012-0-1912"
msgid "To My Dearest Cousin,"
"\n"
"\nThe trip from Deshaan to Stonefalls was difficult and a little hazardous, but I made it safely. The directions that Dethisam provided me with were perfect. I'll make sure to warn the people here about the Llodos plague. And I'll make sure the healers are ready to deal with the illness—at least as well as they're able. You can count on me!"
"\n"
"\nI hope things are going well at the Serk. Try to stay healthy and I'll see you soon."
"\n"
"\nSincerely,"
"\n"
"\nGorvyn"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1912
msgctxt "51188213-0-1912"
msgid "Letter from Gorvyn"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1904
msgctxt "21337012-0-1904"
msgid "Grand Warlord,"
"\n"
"\nThe Moth Priests' plea galls me. Don't they know there's a war on? They cannot expect us to hand over the Elder Scrolls we worked so hard to obtain. You were of course correct to refuse the Moth Priest who is plaguing us."
"\n"
"\nI sent Pavonius away from the temple and gave the guards orders to refuse him entry henceforth. I await only your approval to order a stronger beating each time he shows up. Sooner or later, this will end his pleading."
"\n"
"\n— Protector Galiel"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1904
msgctxt "51188213-0-1904"
msgid "Letter to Grand Warlord Zimmeron"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1903
msgctxt "21337012-0-1903"
msgid "Grand Warlord,"
"\n"
"\nI agree with your decision to retain control of the Elder Scrolls. The scrolls are needed for the war effort, as you say. Handing them to the Moth Priest would only result in them falling into the hands of the Dominion or Pact."
"\n"
"\nI have had temple guards escort Belenius away from the grounds. He will return, but we'll keep kicking him out."
"\n"
"\n— Protector Yseline"
msgstr "돌틴 대장군님,"
"\n"
"\n엘더 스크롤을 계속 통제 하에 두어야 한다는 대장군님의 의견에 동의합니다. 대장군님이 말씀하신 대로, 스크롤은 전쟁 수행에 필요한 존재입니다. 스크롤들을 나방 사제에게 넘겨봤자 결국엔 자치령이나 조약의 손에 떨어질 뿐입니다."
"\n"
"\n사원 경비병들에게 벨레니우스를 구내에서 멀리 호위해 데려가라고 지시해 두었습니다. 다시 돌아오겠지만, 저희는 계속 그를 내보낼 것입니다."
"\n"
"\n— 수호자 이슬린"

#: 51188213-0-1903
msgctxt "51188213-0-1903"
msgid "Letter to Grand Warlord Dortene"
msgstr "돌틴 대장군에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1902
msgctxt "21337012-0-1902"
msgid "Grand Warlord,"
"\n"
"\nThough it makes me uneasy, I concur with your decision to retain control of the Elder Scrolls. Our troops need the boons the scrolls provide. And turning them over to the Moth Priestess would be tantamount to handing them to the Pact or Covenant."
"\n"
"\nWhile I revere the scrolls and honor the Moth Priests for their dedication and study, I have done as you wished and had temple guards escort Theodosia away from the grounds. I have no doubt she will return, however."
"\n"
"\n— Protector Arfire"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1902
msgctxt "51188213-0-1902"
msgid "Letter to Grand Warlord Sorcalin"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1829
msgctxt "21337012-0-1829"
msgid "Greetings Historian Maaga! Your letter will encourage the bandits of Torog's Spite to continue in our endeavors. As you know from studying history, the Bretons and Redguards have betrayed us more callously and more often than any of the other races of Tamriel. Thus, we of Clan Morkul have always been opposed to the decision to join the Daggerfall Covenant. "
"\n"
"\nI specifically vowed to target the Chauvry estate because they still were held in great esteem from the Bretons' other noble houses. Killing them was satisfying, and I am proud to claim credit for the raid for Clan Morkul. I hope this will contribute to the Orcs' withdrawal from this absurd alliance."
"\n"
"\n— Borzugh gro-Morkul"
msgstr "안녕하시오 사학자 Maaga! 당신의 편지는 Torog's Spited의 도적들에게 우리의 노력을 계속해 나갈 용기를 불어넣어줄거요. 역사 연구로 아시다시피, 브레튼과 레드가드는 탐리엘의 다른 종족들보다 훨씬 자주, 냉담하게 우리를 배신했다는 사실을 알고 있을것이오. 그러므로 우리 Morkul 부족은 항상 대거폴 동맹에 가입한다는 결정을 반대해 왔소."
"\n"
"\n나는 특별히 Chauvry 영지를 목표로 하겠다고 맹세했소. 왜냐하면 놈들이 다른 브레튼 귀족 가문들에게 여전히 큰 존경을 받고 있었기 때문이오. 놈들을 죽이는 것은 만족스러웠고, 난 약탈의 공을 Morkul 부족에게 돌릴 수 있게 되어 자랑스럽게 생각하고 있소. 이번 일이 이 우스꽝스러운 연합에서 오크가 탈퇴하는 것에 기여하기를 바라겠소."
"\n"
"\n— Borzugh gro-Morkul"

#: 51188213-0-1829
msgctxt "51188213-0-1829"
msgid "Borzugh's Letter"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1828
msgctxt "21337012-0-1828"
msgid "Hail Historian Maaga! We are honored to receive your request and glad to know there are those in Orsinium who believe in our cause. Our fellow Orcs should know that though we loot from the estates we raid, we do so only to support our ongoing efforts of reparation and glory for our people. The raid on the Chauvry Estate was daring indeed, and we lost several fine Orcs in the battle, but in the end we were victorious, and the Chauvrys are no more. "
"\n"
"\nI was the chief architect of this raid, and I am proud to claim credit for Clan Agluk. As you probably know, most of my clan was killed during the sacking of Orsinium, so it is fitting that I can exact vengeance so many years later for Clan Agluk."
"\n"
"\n— Thorzhul gro-Agluk"
msgstr "사학자 Maaga께 인사드리오! Orsinium에서 우리의 대의를 믿는다는 것을 알게 되어 기쁘구려. 당신의 요청을 명예롭게 받아들이겠소. 우리가 영지를 약탈하긴 했지만,  그것은 배상을 받아내기 위한 노력과 우리 민족의 명예만을 위한 행동이었음을 우리 오크 동포들이 알아야 할 것이오. Chauvry 영지의 약탈은 물론 위험한 일이었고, 우리는 전투에서 몇몇 훌륭한 오크를 잃기도 했지만, 결국 우리는 승리하였고, Chauvry는 더 이상 존재하지 않는다오."
"\n"
"\n난 이 약탈의 주역이었고, Agluk 부족에게 공이 있음을 주장하게 되어 자랑스럽게 생각하고 있소. 당신도 알다시피, 내 부족 대부분은 Orsinium 약탈에서 전사했기 때문에  내가 오랫동안 기다려온, Agluk 부족을 위한 복수를 할 수 있다는 사실은 자명한 것이오."
"\n"
"\n— Thorzhul gro-Agluk"

#: 51188213-0-1828
msgctxt "51188213-0-1828"
msgid "Thorzhul's Letter"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1827
msgctxt "21337012-0-1827"
msgid "Ancalmo, "
"\n"
"\nYou won't believe this. That bumbling Jahadar actually found the skull. It's being held in a cave south of Longhaven. I still can't believe Malangwen managed to lose it just after we took it in the first place. I'm making her come along with me to get it back, with Jahadar to lead the way. If we retrieve it soon enough, we can still follow through with our plan.  Meet us as soon as you can, but be careful. Lucretia will be tracking us by now. Let her come. We'll deal with her as soon as we get the skull back."
"\n"
"\nThis is our chance for the status we deserve."
"\n"
"\n— Dannic"
msgstr "안칼모,"
"\n"
"\n이건 믿기 힘들걸. 그 덤벙대는 자하다가 진짜로 해골을 찾아냈어. 롱헤이븐 남쪽에 있는 동굴에 있다더라고. 우리가 해골을 처음 찾아내자마자 말란그웬이 그걸 잃어버리다니, 아직도 믿기가 힘들다니까. 해골을 되찾으려고 말란그웬을 동행시킬거고, 자하다가 길을 안내해줄거야. 해골을 빨리 되찾으면 지금이라도 우리 계획을 진행시킬 수가 있다고. 최대한 빨리 만나자. 그래도 조심해야 돼. 루크레티아가 지금쯤 우릴 쫓아오고 있을 테니까. 해골을 찾아내자마자 그 여자를 처리할 거야."
"\n"
"\n이건 우리가 마땅히 누릴 지위를 얻어낼 마지막 기회야."
"\n"
"\n— 대닉"

#: 51188213-0-1827
msgctxt "51188213-0-1827"
msgid "Letter from Dannic"
msgstr "대닉이 보낸 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1806
msgctxt "21337012-0-1806"
msgid "My most delightful friend,"
"\n"
"\nI understand you have been having some difficulty of late with your senche-tigers. I want to assure you you have my deepest sympathies. Valenwood can be such a wild place, full of thieves and scoundrels and terrible mystical forces beyond our control."
"\n"
"\nIn fact, it is because of my deep sympathy for your troubles that I wanted you and you alone to know of a lucrative discovery I have recently made. There's an old cave that the Valenwood Bosmer won't go near. They call it the Harridan's Lair because of some old Wood Elf fable. I can assure you it is just a myth. I have been there many times now and never encountered any sort of "Harridan.""
"\n"
"\nBut I digress. My point is, there are senche-tigers in this lair. A great many of them. So many that an enterprising individual such as yourself could easily turn a tidy profit capturing them, breeding them, and selling them to yours truly (and other wise businessmen, of course.) "
"\n"
"\nYou are the only one I've told, but I won't be able to keep this secret exclusive for long!"
"\n"
"\n— Bashshi-ra"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1806
msgctxt "51188213-0-1806"
msgid "Letter from Bashshi-ra"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1803
msgctxt "21337012-0-1803"
msgid "This is the third time this week that my senche-tigers have run off, only to be found butchered near that lamia-infested cave! "
"\n"
"\nIf something is not done about this, I will travel to Marbruk and bring my complaint before the queen herself! Then we will see how long the Thalmor is allowed to throw its weight around Woodhearth!"
"\n"
"\nThe Dominion belongs to the Khajiit as well, not just the Elves. I demand that action be taken at once to investigate the Underroot cavern, and that reparations be made for my lost cats!"
msgstr "내 센치-호랑이가 도망쳤다가 그 라미아가 들끓는 동굴 근처에서 도살당한 채로 발견된게 이번 주에만 벌써 세 번째입니다!"
"\n"
"\n이 사태에 대해서 뭔가 조치를 취하지 않는다면, 난 마브룩으로 가서 여왕 폐하께 내 불만을 집적 전달하겠어요! 그렇게 하면 탈모어가 우드하스에서 얼마나 오랫동안 날뛰어댈 수 있을지 알게 되겠죠!"
"\n"
"\n자치령에는 엘프들만 있는게 아니라 카짓들도 소속되 있다고요. 난 아래뿌리 동굴 조사에 지금 당장 착수할 것을 요구합니다. 내 잃어버린 고양이들에 대한 보상금도 포함해서요!"

#: 51188213-0-1803
msgctxt "51188213-0-1803"
msgid "A Complaint to the Thalmor"
msgstr "탈모어에게 전하는 불만"

#: 21337012-0-1780
msgctxt "21337012-0-1780"
msgid "My Dearest Akash,"
"\n"
"\nThe services you and your tribe have provided are invaluable to my cause. Who but the Wood Orcs could unearth so many remains so quickly? Aside from the Altmer, of course, but they are blind and would move to stop me rather than help."
"\n"
"\nAnd your construction of the altars matched my designs completely! I could not have dreamed of a better partner in this. Who knew I would find one in a Wood Orc?"
"\n"
"\nI hope the payment I've tendered pleases your mercenaries, but more importantly, I hope that our relationship still pleases you. To have you at my side through this, the most important act of my life … has provided a solace that surprises even me."
"\n"
"\nWhen this is over, when Tamriel is free of war, we'll begin our new life together—me as the ruler of a new Altmeri empire, and you as our herald, the leader of our Wood Orc footsoldiers."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1780
msgctxt "51188213-0-1780"
msgid "Letter to Akash"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1756
msgctxt "21337012-0-1756"
msgid "Belya,"
"\n"
"\nYour services are required in Cheydinhal. The rebellion is bearing fruit. You must be our eyes and ears. Take no risks but hasten here."
"\n"
"\n— Iocundus"
msgstr "벨야,"
"\n"
"\n체이딘할에 네 도움이 필요해. 반군 활동이 결실을 맺고 있어. 네가 우리의 눈과 귀가 되어 줘야 해. 위험을 무릅쓰지는 말고, 신속하게 여기로 와 줘."
"\n"
"\n— 로쿤두스"

#: 51188213-0-1756
msgctxt "51188213-0-1756"
msgid "Letter to Belya"
msgstr "벨야에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1640
msgctxt "21337012-0-1640"
msgid "Mother,"
"\n"
"\nI am writing to you from Reaper's March, in the northern part of the forest called Valenwood. The ink used is native to the area, and contains several notable properties not found in Summerset inks. Perhaps you can work out the mathematical equations I've worked into the margins? Consider these elements my evidence that distance from home does not diminish one's mental capacity or acuity. "
"\n"
"\nOur beliefs have rarely coincided, as you know, and so it should come as no surprise to either of us that our life paths diverge so dramatically. Know that I bear you no ill will for your words prior to my departure. "
"\n"
"\nTake my silent response as a sign of my love for you, that I would not speak intemperately. My knowledge of the world has increased a thousandfold with Pircalmo at my side, and I have come to believe that perhaps it is the place of some Altmer to live outside of Summerset. Spreading the gifts we have discovered for ourselves to others."
"\n"
"\nPircalmo and I plan to return to Summerset, and I hope that you find it in your schedule to …."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1640
msgctxt "51188213-0-1640"
msgid "Unfinished Letter to Summerset"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1623
msgctxt "21337012-0-1623"
msgid "Kathner,"
"\n"
"\nBy the time you get this letter, the boat from the Crucible will be just a few days off the coast of Malabal Tor."
"\n"
"\nI know we agreed on a thousand gold per ogre, but I'm willing to offer fifteen hundred if you'd come along. "
"\n"
"\nThese brooding gladiators know nothing of true passion, and it has been far too long since my scales quivered under your supple touch."
"\n"
"\nNo one wants to hear an old Argonian beg, but you're not getting any younger either. Do you really want to spend the rest of your life in a damp cave with those low-lives?"
"\n"
"\n— Beast Master Weerna"
msgstr "캐스너,"
"\n"
"\n네가 이 편지를 받았을 때 쯤이면 시련에서 출발한 배가 며칠 내로 말라발 토르 해안가에 도착할 거야."
"\n"
"\n우리가 오우거 한 마리당 천 골드로 합의했던 건 알지만, 네가 함께 와 준다면 천 오백 골드를 내줄 의향이 있어."
"\n"
"\n이 음울한 싸움꾼들은 진정한 격노를 전혀 모르는 놈들이고, 내 비늘이 네 유연한 손길 아래서 떨린 지도 너무 오래 되었어."
"\n"
"\n늙은 아르고니안의 간청을 듣고 싶은 사람은 없겠지만, 너도 나이가 들어가는 처지잖아. 정말로 네 인생의 나머지를 그 밑바닥 인생들과 함께 축축한 동굴에서 보내고 싶어?"
"\n"
"\n— 짐승 관리인 위어나"

#: 51188213-0-1623
msgctxt "51188213-0-1623"
msgid "Letter to Kathner"
msgstr "캐스너에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1606
msgctxt "21337012-0-1606"
msgid "Remember,"
"\n"
"\nI want my court to be exciting and titillating. I also want our cases to reach their conclusions swiftly. For this reason, please remind all Daedric bailiffs that mortals are weaker and more fragile than Daedra. Our new captives will not easily recover from most injuries, and I want them healthy enough to receive their sentences."
"\n"
"\nDo not damage them. This includes, but is not limited to, severed limbs, flaying, disembowelment, decapitation, and summary execution—at least until judgment has been rendered."
"\n"
"\nPlease, restrain yourselves in the face of these mortal mages, and do not destroy them. I want to play with these toys for as long as possible."
"\n"
"\nNow, let's go serve up some justice! For the glory of Molag Bal!"
"\n"
"\n— Judge Xiven"
msgstr "명심해라,"
"\n"
"\n난 나의 법정이 흥미진진하고 자극적이기를 원한다. 그리고 또한 우리 사건이 신속하게 결론에 다다라야 한다. 이런 연유로, 모든 데이드릭 집행관들은 필멸자들이 나약하며 데이드라보다 부서지기 쉽다는 것을 상기하길 바란다. 우리의 새로운 포로들은 심한 상처에서 회복하기가 쉽지 않고, 난 놈들이 선고를 받을 수 있을 정도로 건강하기를 원한다."
"\n"
"\n놈들을 해치지 마라. 이건 사지 절단, 살갗 벗기기, 배 가르기, 참수, 그리고 즉결 처형을 포함하는 것이지만, 그것에 국한된 것은 아니다. 적어도 판결이 내려질 때까지는 말이다."
"\n"
"\n제발, 필멸의 마법사들 면전에서는 스스로를 억제하고, 놈들을 파괴하지 마라. 난 이 장난감들과 가능한 오래 놀기를 원한다."
"\n"
"\n자, 이제 정의를 실현해 보자! 몰라그 발 님의 영광을 위하여!"
"\n"
"\n— 판사 지븐"

#: 51188213-0-1606
msgctxt "51188213-0-1606"
msgid "A Reminder from the Judge"
msgstr "판사로부터의 주의사항"

#: 21337012-0-1578
msgctxt "21337012-0-1578"
msgid "Headwoman <<1>>,"
"\n"
"\nSome of our homes were damaged in the storm and a great many rats have set upon our crops. While we have the rats in hand, we would inquire as to when we might expect help."
"\n"
"\nNone of us at <<2>> are skilled architects. While a few of us can make simple repairs, we cannot fix everything without help from <<3>>."
"\n"
"\nWe will do what we can while we wait for your word."
"\n"
"\nEver your servant,"
"\n"
"\n— <<4>>"
msgstr "<<1>> 시장님,"
"\n"
"\n저희 집 몇 채가 폭풍으로 손상되었고 엄청나게 많은 쥐떼들이 저희에 농작물을 습격했습니다. 쥐떼들이 문제를 일으키는 동안, 저희가 언제쯤 도움을 받을 수 있을지 문의하고자 합니다."
"\n"
"\n<<2>>에 있는 사람들은 건축에 재능이 없는 사람들입니다. 몇 명이 간단한 수리는 할 수 있겠지만, <<3>>에서의 도움 없이 모든 것을 고칠수는 없습니다."
"\n"
"\n저희가 할 수 있는 일을 하면서 답신을 기다리겠습니다."
"\n"
"\n당신의 영원한 하인,"
"\n"
"\n— <<4>>"

#: 51188213-0-1578
msgctxt "51188213-0-1578"
msgid "Rats in the Crops"
msgstr "농작물의 쥐떼들"

#: 21337012-0-1572
msgctxt "21337012-0-1572"
msgid "<<1>>,"
"\n"
"\nImagine my surprise at leading the herd to the shore and finding riches of the sea spilled upon our doorstep. What a bounty!"
"\n"
"\nSister, bring your wagon to <<2>> with all haste. If we move swiftly, we'll have enough money to start our own plantation!"
"\n"
"\n— <<3>>"
msgstr "<<1>>,"
"\n"
"\n가축들을 데리고 해안가로 가다가 우리 문턱에 흘러들어온 바다의 재물을 봤을 때 내가 얼마나 놀랐을지 상상해 봐. 이 무슨 횡재람!"
"\n"
"\n자매여, 빨리 짐마차를 가지고 <<2>>으로 와. 빠르게 움직이면 우리 소유의 농장을 차릴 돈을 벌 수 있을거야!"
"\n"
"\n— <<3>>"

#: 51188213-0-1572
msgctxt "51188213-0-1572"
msgid "Rakamud's Letter"
msgstr "라카무드의 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1567
msgctxt "21337012-0-1567"
msgid "Honored Clan-Mother,"
"\n"
"\nThe roads are dangerous of late. Bandits attack without fear of reprisal, and harpies, driven to roost by the storm, strike without warning."
"\n"
"\nThese developments have driven this one to hire a pair of mercenaries. Both are hardy walkers, so please triple this one's order this month."
"\n"
"\nPlease, do not worry about protecting the shipment. An escort will arrive before the next crescent."
"\n"
"\nMagrus smile upon your fields by day, Jone and Jode dance over them by night."
"\n"
"\n— <<1>>"
msgstr "존경받는 부족 어머니,"
"\n"
"\n길이 최근들어 위험해졌습니다. 도적들은 보복의 두려움 없이 공격을 가하고, 폭풍으로 횃대에 흘러들어온 하피들은 전조도 없이 습격합니다."
"\n"
"\n이러한 국면 때문에 이 카짓은 용병 두 명을 고용할 수밖에 없었습니다. 둘 다 강건한 자들이니, 이번 달에는 부디 이 카짓의 주문을 세 배로 늘려 주십시오."
"\n"
"\n부디 수송품을 보호하는 문제는 걱정하지 마십시오. 호위대가 다음 초승달 전까지는 도착할 것입니다."
"\n"
"\n낮에는 마그루스께서 당신의 밭에 미소지으시고, 밤에는 존과 조드께서 그 위에서 춤추시기를."
"\n"
"\n— <<1>>"

#: 51188213-0-1567
msgctxt "51188213-0-1567"
msgid "Letter from Karpu-sa"
msgstr "카푸-사가 보낸 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1548
msgctxt "21337012-0-1548"
msgid "To the attention of Captain Albert Marck, with my most humble respects."
"\n"
"\nCaptain, I greatly look forward to gracing Sentinel with my presence next month. I wanted to write to thank you for all the preparations you've made for my arrival. "
"\n"
"\nI wanted to let you know that you've been in touch with someone in my extended organization, a confidante named S'rashi. You may have met him, yes? He's been confirming the bodyguards, the food preparation, etc."
"\n"
"\nHe's also informed me that most of the bodyguards you've hired are former elites from the Ring of Daggers, that unique poisons based on sweetened moon-sugar have been imported from Morrowind, and that representatives of King Fahara'jad's inner circle have been seen entering and leaving your residence late at night."
"\n"
"\nI hope this finds you well. And that my advance team finds you sleeping."
"\n"
"\nRegards,"
"\n"
"\n— Krin Ren-dro"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1548
msgctxt "51188213-0-1548"
msgid "To Captain Marck"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1461
msgctxt "21337012-0-1461"
msgid "My dear, lucky friend Oblan,"
"\n"
"\nYour captain's patriotic foolishness has drawn you the best possible assignment! Imagine, "scouting" for the navy around <<1>>! You'll hit the sands long before any of those officious marine thugs have time to look around."
"\n"
"\nI'm sure you know, most of my supplies come from KR. Since you don't have to pay "shipping fees," you old sea-cat, I expect you to cut me a deal next time you're in H. I'll have a new batch waiting for you, so be sure to get me my raw materials."
"\n"
"\nBetter keep this short—I hear you're sailing with the tides. Best of luck and a safe voyage to you!"
"\n"
"\n— K"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1461
msgctxt "51188213-0-1461"
msgid "Oblan's Letter"
msgstr "오블란의 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1398
msgctxt "21337012-0-1398"
msgid "Dearest,"
"\n"
"\nHave you made any more progress? Are we any closer to discovering the Eye's location? I've sent you some men who owe me favors to assist you. Just direct them as needed."
"\n"
"\nYour loving husband,"
"\n"
"\nQuintus"
"\n"
"\nPS"
"\n"
"\nI do not mean to disrupt your process by hastening you, but I would truly appreciate a swifter pace."
msgstr "내 사랑,"
"\n"
"\n일에 진척은 있었어? 눈이 있는 장소에는 한 걸음 더 가까이 다가간거야? 당신을 도우라고 나한테 신세를 졌던 사람들을 몇 명 보냈어. 필요한 대로 지시하면 돼."
"\n"
"\n당신의 사랑스러운 남편,"
"\n"
"\n퀸투스"
"\n"
"\n추신"
"\n"
"\n당신을 재촉해서 일을 방해하려는건 아니지만, 작업이 빠르게 진행된다면 정말로 고마울 거야."

#: 51188213-0-1398
msgctxt "51188213-0-1398"
msgid "Letter from Quintus"
msgstr "퀸투스가 보낸 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1395
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "21337012-0-1395"
msgid "Fadeel,"
"\n"
"\nHuzal hungers! Many snakes may I tame, but no one tames him! The desert rumbles with his serpentine desires. He craves fresh meat. Send the unwary into Sandblown Mine. Huzal must feast."
"\n"
"\nMirudda"
msgstr "파딜,"
"\n"
"\n"

#: 51188213-0-1395
msgctxt "51188213-0-1395"
msgid "Letter to Fadeel"
msgstr "파딜에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1394
msgctxt "21337012-0-1394"
msgid "Fewer and fewer travelers are using the roads thanks to all the recent trouble. There's no one to send up your way."
"\n"
"\nPlease, give me some time. I have a plan to start trying to send them from the cities. I need a few days to actually get around people though."
"\n"
"\nJust keep that slimy pet of yours far away from me. I'll make sure it has something to eat soon."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1394
msgctxt "51188213-0-1394"
msgid "Letter to Mirudda"
msgstr "미루다에게 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1364
msgctxt "21337012-0-1364"
msgid "Laryaril,"
"\n"
"\nI have received word that the queen is indeed alive and well in Marbruk. This was nothing more than a ruse designed by the Queen's Eyes to expose our presence. The pair you attacked were none other than Razum-dar and <<1)>>, both of whom are well-known enemies to the Veiled Heritance. Despite their efforts, however, we will soon be prepared to execute our plans. "
"\n"
"\nPosing as your sister was effective while it lasted, but it's no longer necessary. Come through the sewers and meet me in the Old Imperial Prison. We have other matters to attend to."
"\n"
"\n— Pelidil"
msgstr "라리아릴,"
"\n"
"\n여왕이 사실은 마브룩에 잘 살아 있다는 전갈을 받았다. 이건 여왕의 눈이 우리 존재를 드러내려고 꾸며낸 책략에 불과해. 네가 공격했던 두 명은 라줌-다르와 <<1>>일 것이다. 둘 다 유명한 베일의 계승단의 적이지. 하지만 놈들의 노력에도 불구하고, 우린 곧 계획을 실행할 준비를 할 수 있을 것이다."
"\n"
"\n그 동안 네 자매 흉내를 낸 것은 효과적이었다. 하지만 더 이상은 필요 없겠지. 하수도를 통해 옛 제국 감옥에서 만나도록 하자. 처리해야 할 다른 문제가 있다."
"\n"
"\n— 펠리딜"

#: 51188213-0-1364
msgctxt "51188213-0-1364"
msgid "Letter to Laryaril"
msgstr "라리아릴에게 쓴 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1350
msgctxt "21337012-0-1350"
msgid "Egg sister,"
"\n"
"\nRain strikes stone as I write this. Thunder echoes, yet no lightning arcs the sky. A strange sort of storm, to be sure."
"\n"
"\nWe had hoped to make the pass at Mud Tree, but weather and hardship have forced us through Alten Corimont. I had not hoped to write until Hissmir and am glad for the diversion."
"\n"
"\nThe storm intensifies. Some chatter about monsters in the dark, but I know better. Here, monsters wait quietly in the shallows. They do not crash through foliage. They do not bellow into the night. When Sithis takes us, we do not hear him coming."
"\n"
"\nMy lids droop like sodden boughs and I must rest. Send my regards to Teemata. May your path be fertile and kissed by sun."
"\n"
"\nStay moist, "
"\n"
"\nOleenla"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1350
msgctxt "51188213-0-1350"
msgid "Letter from Oleenla"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1346
msgctxt "21337012-0-1346"
msgid "Dugrul,"
"\n"
"\nI hope you are well. Father says the land Orcs are cowards to join the Bretons, but I wonder. There is strength in numbers. What does your warchief think?"
"\n"
"\nI am curious about life in the Covenant. What is life in the army like? Have you fought?"
"\n"
"\nA Bosmer told me the Elves have a new queen. Is that true? Did she really say she was going to take back all of Tamriel?"
"\n"
"\nI hear that Duchess Lakana and Duke Nathaniel were married. A Redguard and a Breton? I wonder if the duchess chose this. Oh, to choose your husband! Have you been to Stormhaven?"
"\n"
"\nThe captain of a merchant ship said the Covenant attacked Davon's Watch, the Dark Elf city. He told me the Dark Elves summoned a Daedra, a creature of flame and bone, to fight for them."
"\n"
"\nIs that true? A Daedra? I think the captain was lying to me. I should have killed him."
"\n"
"\nI look forward to your reply. Write more often, cousin, and visit again soon."
"\n"
"\n— Shakra"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1346
msgctxt "51188213-0-1346"
msgid "Shakra's Letter"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1343
msgctxt "21337012-0-1343"
msgid "Lady Delatte,"
"\n"
"\nThese Seamount Orcs are intractable! They have no regard for "Outlanders," as they call us. My entreaties for a trading contract have been ignored. "
"\n"
"\nI know you are loath to give up a possible contract, but nothing is to be gained here! Your informant was correct that no one in Daggerfall has a viable trading contract with these savages. What he left out was that they have no desire for trade."
"\n"
"\nGive me leave to return to Daggerfall. The conditions here are dreadful (they don't even have hot tea!) and I have been forced to sleep in my boat for over a week now. I am ready to come home."
"\n"
"\nYour servant,"
"\n"
"\n— Peverel Stemuseph"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1343
msgctxt "51188213-0-1343"
msgid "Letter from Peverel"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1338
msgctxt "21337012-0-1338"
msgid "Mother,"
"\n"
"\nI wish you could see what I have accomplished here. The city does not reject nature as you might expect. If anything, the relationship is more complex than we could ever have imagined. I know you think I turned my back on you, on everything you taught. I would do anything to help you understand that I have taken what I've learned and found my own place with it, as you always said I should."
"\n"
"\nPlease, come speak with me. I am ready to continue the Accord. I am ready to—"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1338
msgctxt "51188213-0-1338"
msgid "Unfinished Letter"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1333
msgctxt "21337012-0-1333"
msgid "Cousin Idirfa,"
"\n"
"\nSorry for the delay in sending you this letter. I know it might not get delivered for a while, but I wanted to let you know I've had some success. It's been a long journey, but I know it's going to be worth it."
"\n"
"\nThe weather turned bad and we were forced to take shelter in Icehammer's Vault. Not as ideal as a nice warm inn, but at least I can look for some treasure while we're here. As long as I'm quick and quiet, I think I can find some gold and maybe a relic or two. "
"\n"
"\nThe wife is not happy with the situation, of course, but she is patient and understanding. She brought a few books and she's reading to the baby. She prefers religious tomes, but if that's what it takes for her to get through this, that's fine with me."
"\n"
"\nI don't feel good about bringing my family here, but you know how those moneylenders are. I actually feel safer with the family beside me than back in Windhelm where they might get harassed."
"\n"
"\nWe'll return to Fort Amol as soon as we've got enough to pay off my debts. May the Divines watch over you. May they guide and protect us all."
"\n"
"\n— Uggissar"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1333
msgctxt "51188213-0-1333"
msgid "Letter to Idirfa"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1314
msgctxt "21337012-0-1314"
msgid "Sir, I don't know what else I can tell you. If we don't keep the troops out of that old ruin we're going to have trouble."
"\n"
"\nPatrols through Quendeluun are anything but interesting, but we can't have them digging into the deeper tunnels. I can only protect your merchandise if our troops are alive, and we've seen enough down in those old tunnels to turn my hair white."
"\n"
"\nThe deeper tunnels in Quendeluun, called Wansalen, are off limits if the troops want to be paid. Just spread the word next time you're hiring."
msgstr "선생님, 어떻게 설명드려야 할지 모르겠습니다. 저희가 병력을 오래된 유적에 들어가지 못하도록 할 수 없다면, 문제가 생길 겁니다."
"\n"
"\n퀜델룬을 거치는 순찰은 전혀 흥미롭지 않지만, 더 깊은 땅굴로 파고 들어갈 수는 없습니다. 선생님의 상품들은 우리 병력이 살아 있어야만 보호할 수 있고, 저희가 저 오래된 땅굴 아래에서 본 것들은 제 머리를 하얗게 세어버리게 만들기 충분할 정도였습니다."
"\n"
"\n완살렌이라고 불리는 퀜델룬의 깊은 땅굴은, 병력들이 수당을 받고 싶어할 경우에는 출입 금지입니다. 다음 번에 고용하실 때에는 그 말을 전하십시오."

#: 51188213-0-1314
msgctxt "51188213-0-1314"
msgid "Wansalen Tunnels"
msgstr "완살렌 땅굴"

#: 21337012-0-1312
msgctxt "21337012-0-1312"
msgid "Captain,"
"\n"
"\nUnless you have any further objections, we're going to claim that mine. The queen has commanded it, and we have the forces needed to deal with any problems. It's far enough from the road out of Vulkhel Guard that we don't anticipate any problems."
"\n"
"\nFeel free to drop in any time, but we should require no further assistance in this matter."
"\n"
"\nYrs,"
"\n"
"\n— Lennoon"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1312
msgctxt "51188213-0-1312"
msgid "Del's Claim Report"
msgstr "델의 주장 보고서"

#: 21337012-0-1305
msgctxt "21337012-0-1305"
msgid "Captain Lerisa, I see little point in this exercise. What good can come of the crew listing lost possessions? Will Deregor suffer without his lucky dice? Will Haerdun languish without his illustrated Lusty Argonian Maid?"
"\n"
"\nI slave still to scrape together enough gold for a ship, let alone the trivialities the crew lost on the Maiden's Breath. Expecting me to help them replace their lost possessions is ludicrous."
"\n"
"\nFor now, I will file this list where I keep Crenard's extravagant sheafs of recipes. I pray that you come to your senses."
"\n"
"\nOf course, I have already ordered replacements for the make up, clothing, and wigs used to create your many identities."
"\n"
"\nAll this comes for a pittance, and I am certain you will be pleased. Let it never be said that I do not serve you well."
"\n"
"\n—	Telonil, Quartermaster"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1305
msgctxt "51188213-0-1305"
msgid "Letter to Captain Lerisa"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1302
msgctxt "21337012-0-1302"
msgid "I demand that you take immediate action against the traitorous "Captain Helane" and her band of Sea Drakes! They have held the island's only lighthouse for over a year now. In that time, 18 ships have run upon the rocks."
"\n"
"\nI have no doubt that Helane is sabotaging the lighthouse to wreck these ships, leaving her minions to loot the broken holds. While this greatly enriches her, she pays no taxes to you. Is this not a crime?"
"\n"
"\nTrade is your currency, and shipping your life's blood. What do you think will happen as a result of Helane's piracy? Ships will seek harbor elsewhere. Food will stop coming."
"\n"
"\nWill you eat lizards? Mudcrabs? Rats? What will you do when you run out of wool for clothing or leather for shoes? If trade with your fiefdom ceases to be profitable, your new regime will be short indeed."
"\n"
"\nI implore you to gather your Bloody Fists and any fools you can buy. Send your army to Saintsport, rout the Sea Drakes, and take Helane's head before she grows even more powerful."
"\n"
"\nI am your staunchest ally in Glenumbra and will be so as long as our partnership remains profitable. Silence Helane. Let our partnership not wither."
"\n"
"\nIf you leave Helane's greed unchecked, the next head on a pike may be your own. "
"\n"
"\nYour friend,"
"\n"
"\nLady Brunwyn"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1302
msgctxt "51188213-0-1302"
msgid "Letter to Headman Bhosek"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1293
msgctxt "21337012-0-1293"
msgid "Dearest Ehtayah,"
"\n"
"\nI miss you dearly. There are so many people here. They say we'll ride to battle soon. Pray for me that the gods may grant me favor. I want only to see you and our home one more time."
"\n"
"\nBright Moons keep you safe,"
"\n"
"\nIndal"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1293
msgctxt "51188213-0-1293"
msgid "Indal's Letter"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1289
msgctxt "21337012-0-1289"
msgid "My Dearest Thalrinel,"
"\n"
"\nI write to you in the hope that I find you in good health and good spirits. You will need both in the days and weeks to come."
"\n"
"\nI know you were not looking for this much excitement so early in your tenure as Treethane of Silvenar, but the gods challenge us to make us stronger, not to make us more comfortable."
"\n"
"\nCertainly the deaths of Finoriell and her silvenar caught us all by surprise. Some say it's the price we pay for joining the Aldmeri Dominion and involving ourselves in the upheaval of Khenarthi's Roost."
"\n"
"\nI've even heard a few grumblings against the queen, and the Khajiit in general."
"\n"
"\nYou must not let this discontent show at the handfast! I saw your invitation list, and you did exactly what you needed to do. Members of all the Dominion races have been invited and, should they attend, we must treat them as close friends."
"\n"
"\nIf we are to stand against the growing darkness, we must join hands to know who our allies truly are."
"\n"
"\nAll my best,"
"\n"
"\n— E."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1289
msgctxt "51188213-0-1289"
msgid "Letter to Thalrinel"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-128
msgctxt "21337012-0-128"
msgid "Dearest Tavo,"
"\n "
"\nPlease try to return to Sentinel as quickly as you can. If the debt collector comes and we come up short, I fear what he might do. A dozen relics should more than cover our debt."
"\n "
"\nYours forever,"
"\n"
"\nNahrina"
msgstr "친애하는 타보에게,"
"\n"
"\n최대한 빨리 센티넬로 돌아오시길 바랍니다. 만약 빚쟁이가 찾아왔을 때, 돈을 갚지 못한다면 그가 무슨 짓을 할지 너무나도 두렵습니다. 유물 한 다스만 있으면 우리의 빚을 갚을 수 있을 거예요."
"\n"
"\n당신의 영원한 사랑,"
"\n"
"\n나리나"

