#: 21337012-0-1249
msgctxt "21337012-0-1249"
msgid "Petition to the King:"
"\n"
"\nThe Three have become a feared name in Stormhaven, but we come from humble beginnings. Each of us was raised in abject poverty. We learned to steal, but only to scrape by. Our cunning and our collaboration have now earned us great wealth and many followers, but this is not what we sought. "
"\nNor are we fools. We know our days as outlaws are numbered. Though we may elude capture and even expand our enterprise for many years, there will come a day when we will be called to answer for our crimes, and that is a day we hope will never come to pass."
"\n"
"\nAt heart , we are not criminals, and that is why we now seek a pardon from the king. We do not wish to spend the rest of our lives robbing innocent people and running from the Knights of the Flame. We want to turn our operation into a legitimate enterprise. "
"\n"
"\nIn exchange for our pardon, we offer half of all the wealth we have amassed. We have not completed the process of counting it, but rest assured, it is a considerable sum. We hope you take this small gift as proof of our earnestness and that you will give our petition due consideration. "
"\n"
"\nRespectfully and Humbly your Loyal Subjects, "
"\n"
"\nThe Three"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1249
msgctxt "51188213-0-1249"
msgid "The Three's Petition to the King"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1244
msgctxt "21337012-0-1244"
msgid "To His Royal Majesty Emeric, High King of the Daggerfall Covenant,"
"\n"
"\nMy Dear Brother, "
"\n"
"\nAs always, there are several items of note, some related to the security of the kingdom and others of a more personal nature. Please read this privately, and I beg you to exercise discretion in discussing its contents with your advisors. "
"\n"
"\nOf utmost importance are matters related to security here in Alcaire, and unfortunately, though I have strong concerns, I do not have the convenience of a simple or even a consistent element to which I might ascribe Alcaire's troubles of late. "
"\n"
"\nAt the time of my last communication, there were only a few reports of these Vaermina cultists, the Supernal Dreamers. Our shared hopes of this being a short-lived problem were not realized. It seems the cultists have grown even bolder—raiding outlying farms and even recruiting citizens to join their mad ranks. The Knights of the Flame have orders to arrest cult members on sight, but we await further instruction from you on how to deal with a threat that has now spread to other regions of Stormhaven."
"\n"
"\nThe Knights of the Flame continue to prove invaluable allies and staunch defenders of the realm. They have been instrumental in helping me address the cultist problem and in reacting to an attempt made on the duchess' life by an Alik'r assassin. The leader of the Knights of the Flame, one Sir Hughes, suggested that the order assume responsibility for security here at the castle, and I was relieved to agree. It has been a weight lifted off my shoulders. "
"\n"
"\nLastly, and most personally, I wish to express my most sincere gratitude for the arrangement of my marriage to Princess Lakana. Though I feared our union of political necessity would be formal and awkward, nothing could be further from the truth. Her warmth and kindness have created an intimacy between us that I never dreamt possible.  "
"\n"
"\nWe both owe you our gratitude and our undying loyalty."
"\n"
"\nYours truly, "
"\n"
"\nNathaniel"
"\n"
"\nP.S.: The tricks these Redguard women employ in the bedchamber…! Why didn't you warn me, you old dog?"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1244
msgctxt "51188213-0-1244"
msgid "Letter from Duke Nathaniel"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1233
msgctxt "21337012-0-1233"
msgid "Gilles,"
"\n"
"\nThe other day, I was drinking in a pub in Sentinel, and a Breton sitting next to me started talking about politics. I know how much you miss drinking out on the front lines, and believe me, the first few rounds are on me when you get back, but you can't possibly miss listening to some drunken idiot argue about politics."
"\n"
"\nSo this Breton, he starts getting really loud, and he rants about all the reasons we're at war with the Aldmeri Dominion. He talks about economic factors, he talks about resources, he talks about crafting, the guy goes on for what seems like forever, and that's when he stops to take a drink. Which was long enough for me to say two words: "You're wrong.""
"\n"
"\nBecause this guy doesn't know a bloody thing about what it's like fighting the Dominion. Out on the battlefield, they don't care about economics or resources or religion. You're out there for one reason: to kill them before they kill you."
"\n"
"\nEveryone else here knows the truth. For all their lofty Elven pretense, the Aldmeri Dominion only really cares about one thing: conquest. Though they do have standards—they only want to conquer the non-Elves. Like us."
"\n"
"\nSo I told that drunken fool the same thing you told us. Without soldiers like us standing between them and the Imperial throne, the Elves will push and push and push until they hold everything from the shores of High Rock to the heart of Cyrodiil."
"\n"
"\nAny Altmer who looks at a Breton, he's going to see a human. Any Altmer who looks at a Redguard like me … well, there's no way around it, he pretty much knows I'm a Redguard. And there's no mistaking an Orc. Ain't none of us Elves."
"\n"
"\nLife is getting a little more relaxed in the city now, since everyone has pretty much accepted we're at war, and there's still the occasional High Elf in the streets who can go about his business without a fight. It's still sane enough that they can walk around in public. Inside the city walls, I've seen a handful of High Elves walking into the Mages Guild, selling their wares, and even ordering those fruity wines they like so much, and as long as the city watch is keeping the peace, we'll be peaceful."
"\n"
"\nBut when we're in the field, we don't hesitate. Everyone—except that one loudmouthed Breton I put in his place—everyone knows we're holding the line against the Altmer. And when we come back to town in one piece, we're going to be heroes, and we'll be shouting and drinking in that tavern. "
"\n"
"\nSo make sure you come back in one piece."
"\n"
"\nStay safe,"
"\n"
"\nDuqaq af-Wazif"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1233
msgctxt "51188213-0-1233"
msgid "A Soldier's Letter"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1210
msgctxt "21337012-0-1210"
msgid "My dearest, "
"\n"
"\nAnother month come and gone, and still no sign of Falinesti. I received letters from the Summer site with the same news. I fear we may never see the city in our lifetime. How does this happen? How does an entire city just vanish? Questions we've asked a hundred times and still no answer."
"\n"
"\nPerhaps we should abandon our watch once and for all. We had lives, once. Lives we could return to. Please write soon and let me know what you think. I miss you and the children. We could reunite in Elden Root and at least be together—for a time. "
"\n"
"\nWrite soon,"
"\nAltholmir"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1210
msgctxt "51188213-0-1210"
msgid "Letter from Altholmir"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1208
msgctxt "21337012-0-1208"
msgid "Miners,"
"\n"
"\nThe Mages Guild has decided to terminate this operation."
"\n"
"\nIt looks like Giara has been wasting our time. We've found three geodes the whole time we were here. Two of them shattered when she tried to use them as soul gems. I think it's because she lacks the skill to make them correctly. And apparently, there's a reason why most soul gems are crystals. "
"\n"
"\nI hate losing lives for the sake of some mage's whim. This mine isn't profitable enough, so we're out. Pack your things and leave this pit. We're going back to Koeglin to figure out the next job."
"\n"
"\nWe need to get out of here before anyone else gets killed."
"\n"
"\nDrop everything. Get moving."
"\n"
"\n— The Boss"
msgstr "광산 노동자들에게"
"\n"
"\n마법사 길드는 이 작업을 중지하기로 결정했다."
"\n"
"\n기아라는 우리들의 시간을 내다 버린 것 같다. 여기에 있는 동안 모두 세 개의 수정돌을 찾았다. 그 중 두 개는 그녀가 소울젬으로 사용하려 했을 때 산산조각이 나버렸다. 그녀는 분명 그것을 사용할 능력이 없었으리라. 아무래도 많은 소울젬이 크리스탈 형태로 있는 것은 뭔가 이유가 있는 것 같다."
"\n"
"\n마법사들의 생각으로 목숨을 희생할 수는 없다. 이 광산에서 충분한 이익을 얻지 못했기 때문에, 사업을 중지하기로 했다. 소지품을 정리하고 이 동굴에서 나가길 바란다. 다음 일을 찾기 위해 코이그린에 돌아갈 예정이다."
"\n"
"\n사망자가 나오기 전에, 전원 여기서 피난하도록."
"\n"
"\n모든 것을 버리고, 앞으로 나아가자."
"\n"
"\n— 작업 대장으로부터"

#: 51188213-0-1208
msgctxt "51188213-0-1208"
msgid "Foreman's Letter"
msgstr "작업대장의 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1206
msgctxt "21337012-0-1206"
msgid "Fellows,"
"\n"
"\nThank you very much for all your hard work. We appreciate your willingness to deal with risk and your industrious labor. Unfortunately, you need to focus on greater discrimination when collecting our crystals."
"\n"
"\nI hate to tell you this, but the specimens you've been mining do not meet our agreed requirements. We've been comparing them against the samples we supplied, and they're somewhat lacking. These crystals lack the volume to make adequate soul gems. They are insufficient. If your yield does not increase, we may need to reconsider this enterprise."
"\n"
"\nGiara is experimenting with the two "hollow stones" you acquired, but she needs more to get definitive results. In fact, she needs considerably more than two. We can sell the discarded crystals you found for a marginal amount of profit, but not enough to defray our expenses. "
"\n"
"\nIn short, we need more geodes. If you can find a sufficient quantity, we may have a chance of salvaging this operation after the considerable expense of hiring you."
"\n"
"\nRespectfully,"
"\n"
"\nThe Wayrest Mages Guild"
msgstr "여러분들께"
"\n"
"\n항상 협력에 감사드립니다. 위험한 일에 대해 여러분들의 의욕과 근면성은 실로 감탄스러울 정도입니다. 하지만, 크리스탈을 회수할 때는 조금 더 식별에 주의를 부탁드립니다."
"\n"
"\n죄송하지만, 여러분들이 지금까지 발굴하신 크리스탈은 저희들이 찾던 품질에 달하지 못하였습니다. 저희들이 가지고 있는 표본과 비교해보면 어떤 크리스탈이든간에 부족한 부분이 있습니다. 소울젬으로 사용하기 위해서는 이 크기로서는 너무 작습니다. 불충분합니다. 산출량이 늘어나지 않는다면, 이 사업계획을 재검토해야 할 것입니다."
"\n"
"\n기아라는 여러분들이 발굴하진 두 개의 '거짓의 돌'을 사용해 실험을 하고 있습니다. 하지만, 확정적인 결과를 얻기 위해서는 더욱 많은 조사가 필요합니다. 즉, 훨씬 더 많은 돌이 필요한 것입니다. 여러분들께서 찾아주신 불필요한 크리스탈을 판다면 다소의 이익은 발생하겠으나, 그것만으로는 경비를 충당할 수 없습니다."
"\n"
"\n즉, 더 많은 수정 돌이 필요합니다. 충분한 양이 발굴되면 이 사업을 구제할 수 있을 것 입니다."
"\n"
"\n그럼 안녕히,"
"\n"
"\n웨이레스트 마법사 길드 "

#: 51188213-0-1206
msgctxt "51188213-0-1206"
msgid "Further Missive from the Mages"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1205
msgctxt "21337012-0-1205"
msgid "Fellows,"
"\n"
"\nThank you again for accepting our patronage. We know this excavation will entail a degree of risk, but I am certain you'll find our compensation quite generous."
"\n"
"\nAgain, we are paying you to mine these caves for a very specific variety of crystal. Your foreman has samples, and your remuneration will depend on how well your specimens match those samples. You can keep anything you find that isn't a crystal, as long as you can deliver what we need on time."
"\n"
"\nYour foreman is also responsible for hiring armed guards to protect you from anything monstrous you unearth. We assume no liability for deaths or injuries incurred, just as we trust your judgment to dig deeper without invoking the wrath of the local wildlife. That is precisely why we hired you."
"\n"
"\nIn addition to crystals, we want to acquire a exotic variety of rock. It is known as a "geode." Your foreman has one sample for your perusal. We want these "hollow stones" unbroken and unblemished."
"\n"
"\nOne of our scholars, Giara, has theories about the relationship between their spherical shape and their suitability as soul gems. We believe their spherical design bestows a much greater capacity for animus storage than traditional crystalline shapes, but only if they are intact."
"\n"
"\nNo doubt your diligent efforts will be mutually profitable to both of us."
"\n"
"\nEnthusiastically,"
"\n"
"\nThe Wayrest Mages Guild"
msgstr "여러분들께"
"\n"
"\n협력에 감사드립니다. 이 발굴작업이 약간의 위험을 안고 있다는 것은 알고 있지만, 그 노력은 반드시 보상받을 것 입니다."
"\n"
"\n한 말씀 더 드리자면, 저희들은 이 동굴을 발굴해 특수한 크리스탈을 발견하기 위해 여러분들께 보수를 지불하고 있습니다. 작업대장이 표본을 가지고 있습니다. 여러분들에 대한 보수는 그 표본과 적합도가 높을 수록 보수도 증가할 것입니다. 크리스탈 이외의 것이라도 필요한 시간까지 도착한다면, 반드시 보관해 둬 주십시오."
"\n"
"\n또한 작업대장은 위험한 생물이 나타날 경우에 대비해, 위병대를 고용하여 여러분들을 지킬 의무가 있습니다. 여러분이 사망하거나 다치시더라도 저희들은 일절의 책임을 지지 않습니다. 여러분들이라면, 현지의 야생동물을 위협하는 일 없이, 깊게 발굴해 나아갈 수 있으리라 믿고 있습니다. 그렇기 때문에 여러분들을 고용한 것입니다."
"\n"
"\n저희들은 크리스탈뿐만 아닌 진귀한 돌도 발굴하고 있습니다. '수정돌'이라 불리는 돌입니다. 작업대장이 표본을 가지고 있으니 확인해주세요. 흠집이나 더럽혀지지 않은 상태의 돌을 찾아 주십시오."
"\n"
"\n학자 기아라는 그 공과 같은 형태와, 소울젬으로서의 적합성의 사이에는 일련의 관계가 있다고 생각하고 있습니다. 일반적인 크리스탈의 형상보다도 공과 같은 형상을 하고 있는 쪽이 훨씬 더 많이 저장되어 있을 가능성이 있습니다. 단 흠집이 없는 것이어야 합니다."
"\n"
"\n여러분들이 성실하게 일해주신다면 분명 서로 이익이 될 것 입니다."
"\n"
"\n진심을 담아,"
"\n"
"\n웨이레스트 마법사 길드 "

#: 51188213-0-1205
msgctxt "51188213-0-1205"
msgid "Missive from the Mages Guild"
msgstr "마법사 길드에서 온 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1101
msgctxt "21337012-0-1101"
msgid "Son, I write this to you lest the worst happen before you return to your senses, in which case this may be the only way I can speak to you. "
"\n"
"\nThe woman Adima is a venomous snake who has poisoned your thoughts and darkened your heart. Indeed, when I see the bloodlust in her eye, I doubt she is a true woman at all. "
"\n"
"\nYou are strong, my son, and wise in the world's ways, for we have taught you all and held naught back. For you to succumb to the wiles of such a creature sorcery must be involved, for no ordinary human could sway you so from the path of clear thought and action. "
"\n"
"\nAs you read this, let it be as a window opening in your mind, as a clean wind blowing through your heart. Awaken, Hosni, from your dreams of blood. Abjure this Adima, and seek your penitence in whatever task Sister Safia shall set for you. For she will tell you what is right and best to hear, no matter how hard it may be to listen. "
"\n"
"\nYour Mother, Who Loves You Always, "
"\n"
"\n— Sirali"
msgstr "아들아, 네가 정신을 차리기 전에 최악의 일이 생길까 걱정이 되어 이 편지를 쓴다. 지금으로서는 이게 내가 너에게 말을 전할 수 있는 유일한 방법인 것 같구나."
"\n"
"\n그 아디마라는 여자는 네 생각에 독을 주입하고 네 마음을 어둡게 하는 독사란다. 내가 그녀의 눈에서 살기를 봤을 때, 나는 그녀가 진짜 여성이 아닐 거라는 생각이 들었다."
"\n"
"\n아들아, 우리는 너에게 모든 것을 가르쳤고 불필요한 것은 말하지 않았다. 때문에 너는 강하고 현명하단다. 네가 그런 생명 마법의 술책에 굴복하게 된 것에는 어떤 음모가 있을 거다. 평범한 사람은 너의 확신 있는 생각과 행동을 그렇게 흔들 수 없기 때문이란다."
"\n"
"\n네가 이 편지를 읽을 때, 네 마음에 창문을 열어 네 심장으로 깨끗한 바람이 들어오게 두려무나. 피의 꿈에서 깨어나렴, 호스니. 아비나를 버리고 사피아 자매가 널 위해 준비한 일을 하며 인내심을 찾으려무나. 아무리 듣기 힘들어도 그녀가 너에게 무엇이 옳은지 무엇을 가장 들어야 하는지 알려줄 것이기 때문이다."
"\n"
"\n너를 항상 사랑하는 어머니,"
"\n"
"\nㅡ시라리"

#: 51188213-0-1101
msgctxt "51188213-0-1101"
msgid "Letter to Hosni"
msgstr "호스니에게 쓴 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1088
msgctxt "21337012-0-1088"
msgid "Three servants and no fewer than six family members have been murdered in a fashion suggesting the vilest witchcraft. "
"\n"
"\nSeveral months ago, one of our patrols captured and executed a coven of Ice Witches from the north. We now have evidence that one of their kind escaped. I fear that she entered the castle for the celebration, disguised as a commoner, to enact her vengeance. Have trusted guards and servants seal all entrances to the castle immediately. All guests from the surrounding villages should be immediately placed under guard and restrained if necessary. "
"\n"
"\nThis Ice Witch, Drodda, is aligned with the darkest powers of Oblivion and should be considered extremely dangerous. Kill her on sight."
"\n"
"\nAgomar, Lord of Direfrost"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1088
msgctxt "51188213-0-1088"
msgid "To the Captain of the Guard"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1076
msgctxt "21337012-0-1076"
msgid "My friend,"
"\n"
"\nWe have a new employer. Clean out the werewolves, and he'll pay hefty coin for every ear you bring back."
"\n"
"\nMake it quick and quiet. Don't want trouble from anyone."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1076
msgctxt "51188213-0-1076"
msgid "Altered Missive"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-106
msgctxt "21337012-0-106"
msgid "You shouldn't have to be reminded of our agreement, but this one seems to find herself in a position where she has to. "
"\n"
"\nWe haven't had any fresh travelers through here for weeks. If we don't have travelers to ambush, we don't get any gold or valuables, which in turn means you get nothing."
"\n"
"\nYou have four days to send goods our way before Huzal starts to get hungry."
"\n"
"\n— Mirudda"
msgstr "당신에게 우리의 합의를 상기시킬 필요는 없지만, 그녀에게는 자신이 어떤 처지인지를 알려줘야 할 것 같군."
"\n"
"\n지난 1주일이나 아무 여행자도 만나지 못했어. 약탈할 여행자를 찾지 못하면 돈이나 귀중품을 얻을 수 없고, 그 말은 즉 당신한테 아무것도 안 들어온단 얘기지."
"\n"
"\n4일을 주겠다, Huzal이 배고파지기 전에 우리에게 물건을 보내라."
"\n"
"\n— Mirudda"

#: 51188213-0-106
msgctxt "51188213-0-106"
msgid "Letter from Mirudda"
msgstr "Mirudda가 보내는 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1056
msgctxt "21337012-0-1056"
msgid "My Dear Captain,"
"\n"
"\nIt appears I missed you at home. I did, however, have the pleasure of meeting six or so of your men. Tough as they appeared, I'm afraid they simply couldn't hold their liquor."
"\n"
"\nI do hope to make your acquaintance again soon. I really need to thank you for what you've done to my ship and crew."
"\n"
"\nPleasant dreams."
"\n"
"\n— Captain Lerisa"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1056
msgctxt "51188213-0-1056"
msgid "Letter to Captain Helane"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1047
msgctxt "21337012-0-1047"
msgid "Denskar,"
"\n"
"\nI'm gone. I'm not coming back. You're going to hear rumors about me. I'm ashamed to say they're true."
"\n"
"\nAfter Tryn died, I lost my way. I will have no more to do with the Worm Cult, but that doesn't make up for the things I did."
"\n"
"\nPlease take care of Littrek. I know he won't understand. I pray that you will someday. I won't ever stop loving you, Den, but you should move on. I've done too much wrong to ever come back."
"\n"
"\nAll my love,"
"\n"
"\n—	Aera"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1047
msgctxt "51188213-0-1047"
msgid "Aera's Letter to Denskar"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1046
msgctxt "21337012-0-1046"
msgid "Tryn,"
"\n"
"\nSoon, you're going to hear very bad things about me. I wish I could tell you they weren't true. But they are. All I can say is that I know I did wrong."
"\n"
"\nI know you're disappointed. I can't ever make this up to you, but please, remember I love you. And I'm sorry."
"\n"
"\n—	Mother"
msgstr "트린에게,"
"\n"
"\n곧, 나에 대해 아주 나쁜 말을 듣게 될 거야. 그것들이 사실이 아니라고 말해줄 수 있으면 좋겠다. 하지만 사실이야. 내가 할 수 있는 말은, 내가 잘못을 저질렀단 걸 알고 있다는 것 뿐이란다."
"\n"
"\n실망한 거 알아. 무슨 말을 해도 너에게 보상이 되지 못하겠지만, 제발, 엄마가 널 사랑한다는 것을 기억해다오. 그리고 미안하다."
"\n"
"\n—	엄마가"

#: 51188213-0-1046
msgctxt "51188213-0-1046"
msgid "Aera's Letter to Tryn"
msgstr "아에라가 트린에게 쓴 편지"

#: 21337012-0-1034
msgctxt "21337012-0-1034"
msgid "When you're able to slip away unnoticed, find the others in the ruins by the river. I ordered the soldiers to avoid the area, so you should have no trouble. Destroy this note after you read it, Durel Gilveni, or I will burn you to cinders."
msgstr "들키지 않고 몰래 빠져 나올 때 강 근처 폐허 속에서  다른 사람들을 찾아라. 난 병사들에게 그 지역을 가지 말라고 명령했다. 그래서 너는 아무 문제가 없을거야. 이 메모를 읽은 뒤 태워라. Durel Gilveni, 나는 너를 태워버릴 것이다."

#: 51188213-0-1034
msgctxt "51188213-0-1034"
msgid "Private Dispatch (Secret!)"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1028
msgctxt "21337012-0-1028"
msgid "YOU PIG!!!!"
"\n"
"\nYou are more of a pig than our pigs! And with my sister!!!! I hope you die a horrible death, screaming for mercy while animals root in your entrails, PIG!"
"\n"
"\nI am taking the children and going to my sister's. No, not that one, she's all yours. My other sister."
"\n"
"\nDIE, DIE, DIE!!!!"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1028
msgctxt "51188213-0-1028"
msgid "Furious Letter"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1017
msgctxt "21337012-0-1017"
msgid "Captain,"
"\n"
"\nHere is a sample of some of the Master's most recent thoughts on war. As you know, his observations have inspired a generation of Dark Elf commanders. May they do the same for you."
"\n"
"\nHe wishes you much success in the Cyrodiil campaign."
"\n"
"\n- - - - -"
"\n"
"\nThe greatest leader holds his most powerful spell in reserve. "
"\n"
"\nTo understand your opponent, wear their armor. Know where it is weakest."
"\n"
"\nHide your sharpest blade behind your softest cloak."
"\n"
"\nKnow where the ground is firm, and where it is soft. You will always be the victor."
"\n	"
"\nEvery battle is an illusion. The strength of that illusion is up to you."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1017
msgctxt "51188213-0-1017"
msgid "The Sharpest Blade"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1007
msgctxt "21337012-0-1007"
msgid "Dearest Vigrod,"
"\n"
"\nWe were all thrilled to hear of your latest promotion! Your father still says you should have stayed on the farm, of course, but he's secretly proud to have a son in the Companions. Don't tell him I said so, though."
"\n"
"\nThat sweet little Gurilda stopped by the house yesterday. She brought over some venison and a jug of Four-Eye Grog from her pa. She knows Dad has a sweet spot for the grog. And since he hurt his back and can't hunt, the venison is very welcome."
"\n"
"\nThat girl's going to make someone a good hearth-wife someday soon. Could be you, if you came out of your shell a bit and actually talked to her. Pretty face, good hips, a fine farm to inherit, quite a catch all told. But no more about that."
"\n"
"\nNow don't you worry about us, we'll be fine. Pa can't work the farm like he used to, but we're talking about hiring a hand or two to help out. With all the refugees streaming past here day and night, help is easy to find."
"\n"
"\nPlease try not to get stabbed or slashed any more. You weren't the handsomest of lads to start with. A few scars build character but too many will ruin what looks you have. "
"\n"
"\nAll my love,"
"\n"
"\nMother"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1007
msgctxt "51188213-0-1007"
msgid "Letter to Vigrod"
msgstr ""